#: src/intro.md:1
msgid ""
"![Just One Single History](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/josh-project/"
"josh/master/splash.jpg)"
msgstr ""
"![Just One Single History](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/josh-project/"
"josh/master/splash.jpg)"

#: src/intro.md:3
msgid ""
"Josh combines the advantages of monorepos with those of multirepos by "
"leveraging a blazingly-fast, incremental, and reversible implementation of "
"git history filtering."
msgstr ""
"Josh 结合了 monorepo 与 multirepo 各自的优势，借助极速、增量且可逆的 git 历史"
"过滤实现来实现这一目标。"

#: src/intro.md:6
msgid "Concept"
msgstr "概念"

#: src/intro.md:8
msgid ""
"Traditionally, history filtering has been viewed as an expensive operation "
"that should only be performed to fix issues with a repository, such as "
"purging big binary files or removing accidentally-committed secrets, or as "
"part of a migration to a different repository structure, like switching from "
"multirepo to monorepo (or vice versa)."
msgstr ""
"传统上，历史过滤被视为一种开销高昂的操作，只应在修复仓库问题时执行，例如清除"
"大型二进制文件或删除意外提交的密钥，或作为迁移到不同仓库结构（如从 multirepo "
"切换到 monorepo，或反之）的一部分。"

#: src/intro.md:13
msgid ""
"The implementation shipped with git (`git-filter branch`) is only usable as "
"a once-in-a-lifetime last resort for anything but tiny repositories."
msgstr ""
"git 自带的实现（`git-filter branch`）对于非小型仓库而言，只能作为生命周期中一次性的"
"最后手段来使用。"

#: src/intro.md:16
msgid ""
"Faster versions of history filtering have been implemented, such as [git-"
"filter-repo](https://github.com/newren/git-filter-repo) or the [BFG repo "
"cleaner](https://rtyley.github.io/bfg-repo-cleaner/). Those, while much "
"faster, are designed for doing occasional, destructive maintenance tasks, "
"usually with the idea already in mind that once the filtering is complete "
"the old history should be discarded."
msgstr ""
"更快版本的历史过滤实现已经问世，例如 [git-filter-repo](https://github.com/"
"newren/git-filter-repo) 或 [BFG repo cleaner](https://rtyley.github.io/"
"bfg-repo-cleaner/)。这些工具虽然快得多，但其设计初衷是用于偶尔执行的破坏性维护"
"任务，通常在执行前就已预设：一旦过滤完成，旧历史将被丢弃。"

#: src/intro.md:22
msgid "The idea behind `josh` started with two questions:"
msgstr "`josh` 背后的理念源于两个问题："

#: src/intro.md:24
msgid ""
"What if history filtering could be so fast that it can be part of a normal, "
"everyday workflow, running on every single push and fetch without the user "
"even noticing?"
msgstr ""
"如果历史过滤可以快到足以成为日常工作流程的一部分，在每次 push 和 fetch 时运行"
"而用户甚至无所察觉，那会怎样？"

#: src/intro.md:26
msgid "What if history filtering was a non-destructive, reversible operation?"
msgstr "如果历史过滤是一种非破坏性、可逆的操作，那会怎样？"

#: src/intro.md:28
msgid ""
"Under those two premises a filter operation stops being a maintenance task. "
"It seamlessly relates histories between repos, which can be used by "
"developers and CI systems interchangeably in whatever way is most suitable "
"to the task at hand."
msgstr ""
"基于这两个前提，过滤操作不再是维护任务，而是无缝地关联各仓库之间的历史，"
"开发者和 CI 系统可以根据手头任务以最合适的方式互换使用。"

#: src/intro.md:32
msgid "How is this possible?"
msgstr "这是如何实现的？"

#: src/intro.md:34
msgid ""
"Filtering history is a highly predictable task: The set of filters that tend "
"to be used for any given repository is limited, such that the input to the "
"filter (a git branch) only gets modified in an incremental way. Thus, by "
"keeping a persistent cache between filter runs, the work needed to re-run a "
"filter on a new commit (and its history) becomes proportional to the number "
"of changes since the last run; The work to filter no longer depends on the "
"total length of the history. Additionally, most filters also do not depend "
"on the size of the trees."
msgstr ""
"过滤历史是一项高度可预测的任务：针对任意给定仓库所使用的过滤器集合是有限的，"
"过滤器的输入（git 分支）也只以增量方式被修改。因此，通过在两次过滤运行之间保留"
"持久化缓存，对新提交（及其历史）重新运行过滤器所需的工作量，就与自上次运行以来"
"的变更数量成正比；过滤工作量不再取决于历史总长度。此外，大多数过滤器也不依赖"
"目录树的大小。"

#: src/intro.md:41
msgid ""
"What has long been known to be true for performing merges also applies to "
"history filtering: The more often it is done the less work it takes each "
"time."
msgstr ""
"长期以来对合并操作所认知的规律，同样适用于历史过滤：执行得越频繁，每次所需的"
"工作量就越少。"

#: src/intro.md:44
msgid ""
"To guarantee filters are reversible we have to restrict the kind of filter "
"that can be used; It is not possible to write arbitrary filters using a "
"scripting language like is allowed in other tools. To still be able to cover "
"a wide range of use cases we have introduced a domain-specific language to "
"express more complex filters as a combination of simpler ones. Apart from "
"guaranteeing reversibility, the use of a DSL also enables pre-optimization "
"of filter expressions to minimize both the amount of work to be done to "
"execute the filter as well as the on-disk size of the persistent cache."
msgstr ""
"为了保证过滤器的可逆性，我们必须限制可使用的过滤器类型；不允许像其他工具那样"
"使用脚本语言编写任意过滤器。为了仍能覆盖广泛的使用场景，我们引入了一种领域特定"
"语言（DSL），将更复杂的过滤器表达为简单过滤器的组合。除了保证可逆性之外，使用"
"DSL 还能对过滤器表达式进行预优化，以最小化执行过滤所需的工作量以及持久化缓存的"
"磁盘占用。"

#: src/usecases.md:4
msgid "Partial cloning"
msgstr "部分克隆"

#: src/usecases.md:6
msgid ""
"Reduce scope and size of clones by treating subdirectories of the monorepo "
"as individual repositories."
msgstr ""
"通过将 monorepo 的子目录视为独立仓库，缩减克隆的范围和体积。"

#: src/usecases.md:9 src/usecases.md:76
msgid "Using the `josh` CLI:"
msgstr "使用 `josh` 命令行工具："

#: src/usecases.md:10
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ josh clone https://git.example.com/monorepo.git :/path/to/library ./"
"library\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"$ josh clone https://git.example.com/monorepo.git :/path/to/library ./"
"library\n"
"```"

#: src/usecases.md:14 src/usecases.md:81
msgid "Or via a shared [josh-proxy](./reference/proxy.md):"
msgstr "或通过共享的 [josh-proxy](./reference/proxy.md)："

#: src/usecases.md:15
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ git clone http://josh/monorepo.git:/path/to/library.git\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"$ git clone http://josh/monorepo.git:/path/to/library.git\n"
"```"

#: src/usecases.md:19
msgid ""
"The partial repo will act as a normal git repository but only contain the "
"files found in the subdirectory and only commits affecting those files. The "
"partial repo supports both fetch as well as push operation."
msgstr ""
"部分仓库的行为与普通 git 仓库相同，但只包含该子目录中的文件以及影响这些文件的"
"提交。部分仓库同时支持 fetch 和 push 操作。"

#: src/usecases.md:23
msgid ""
"This helps not just to improve performance on the client due to having fewer "
"files in the tree, it also enables collaboration on parts of the monorepo "
"with other parties utilizing git's normal distributed development features. "
"For example, this makes it easy to mirror just selected parts of your repo "
"to public github repositories or specific customers."
msgstr ""
"这不仅有助于因工作树中文件更少而提升客户端性能，还能利用 git 的普通分布式开发"
"功能，与其他方就 monorepo 的特定部分开展协作。例如，这使得仅将仓库中选定的部分"
"镜像到公开的 github 仓库或特定客户变得轻而易举。"

#: src/usecases.md:30
msgid "Project composition / Workspaces"
msgstr "项目组合 / Workspace"

#: src/usecases.md:32
msgid ""
"Simplify code sharing and dependency management. Beyond just subdirectories, "
"Josh supports filtering, re-mapping and composition of arbitrary virtual "
"repositories from the content found in the monorepo."
msgstr ""
"简化代码共享和依赖管理。Josh 不仅支持子目录，还支持对 monorepo 中的内容进行"
"过滤、重新映射和组合，构建任意虚拟仓库。"

#: src/usecases.md:36
msgid ""
"The mapping itself is also stored in the repository and therefore versioned "
"alongside the code."
msgstr "该映射本身也存储在仓库中，因此与代码一起进行版本管理。"

#: src/usecases.md:39
msgid ""
"Multiple projects, depending on a shared set of libraries, can thus live "
"together in a single repository. This approach is commonly referred to as "
"“monorepo”, and was popularized by [Google](https://people.engr.ncsu.edu/"
"ermurph3/papers/seip18.pdf), Facebook or Twitter to name a few."
msgstr ""
"多个依赖同一组共享库的项目，因此可以共存于单个仓库中。这种方式通常被称为 "
"monorepo，并由 [Google](https://people.engr.ncsu.edu/ermurph3/papers/seip18.pdf)、"
"Facebook 或 Twitter 等公司推广普及。"

#: src/usecases.md:44
msgid ""
"In this example, two projects (`project1` and `project2`) coexist in the "
"`central` monorepo."
msgstr "在本示例中，两个项目（`project1` 和 `project2`）共存于 `central` monorepo 中。"

#: src/usecases.md:74
msgid "Workspaces act as normal git repos."
msgstr "Workspace 的行为与普通 git 仓库相同。"

#: src/usecases.md:77
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ josh clone https://git.example.com/central.git :workspace=workspaces/"
"project1 ./project1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"$ josh clone https://git.example.com/central.git :workspace=workspaces/"
"project1 ./project1\n"
"```"

#: src/usecases.md:82
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ git clone http://josh/central.git:workspace=workspaces/project1.git\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"$ git clone http://josh/central.git:workspace=workspaces/project1.git\n"
"```"

#: src/usecases.md:86
msgid ""
"Each of the subprojects defines a `workspace.josh` file, defining the "
"mapping between the original central.git repository and the hierarchy in use "
"inside of the project."
msgstr ""
"每个子项目均定义一个 `workspace.josh` 文件，用于描述原始 central.git 仓库与"
"项目内部目录结构之间的映射关系。"

#: src/usecases.md:88
msgid ""
"In this setup, project1 and project2 can seamlessly depend on the latest "
"version of library1, while only checking out the part of the central "
"monorepo that's needed for their purpose. What's more, any changes to a "
"shared module will be synced in both directions."
msgstr ""
"在此配置下，project1 和 project2 可以无缝依赖 library1 的最新版本，同时只签出"
"central monorepo 中其所需的部分。更重要的是，对共享模块的任何修改都会双向同步。"

#: src/usecases.md:91
msgid ""
"If a developer of the library1 pushed a new update, both projects will get "
"the new version, and the developer will be able to check if they broke any "
"test. If a developer of project1 needs to update the library, the changes "
"will be automatically shared back into central, and project2."
msgstr ""
"若 library1 的开发者推送了新的更新，两个项目都会收到新版本，该开发者也能据此"
"检查是否破坏了任何测试。若 project1 的开发者需要更新该库，其变更将被自动同步回"
"central 和 project2。"

#: src/usecases.md:94
msgid "Simplified CI/CD"
msgstr "简化 CI/CD"

#: src/usecases.md:96
msgid ""
"With everything stored in one repo, CI/CD systems only need to look into one "
"source for each particular deliverable. However in traditional monorepo "
"environments dependency management is handled by the build system. Build "
"systems are usually tailored to specific languages and need their input "
"already checked out on the filesystem. So the question:"
msgstr ""
"将所有内容存储在一个仓库中后，CI/CD 系统对每个特定交付物只需查看一个来源。"
"然而，在传统的 monorepo 环境中，依赖管理由构建系统负责。构建系统通常针对特定"
"语言定制，并需要其输入已签出到文件系统。因此问题来了："

#: src/usecases.md:103
msgid ""
"\"What deliverables are affected by a given commit and need to be rebuild?\""
msgstr "\"哪些交付物受某次提交影响并需要重新构建？\""

#: src/usecases.md:105
msgid ""
"cannot be answered without cloning the entire repository and understanding "
"how the languages used handle dependencies."
msgstr ""
"在不克隆整个仓库并了解所用语言如何处理依赖的情况下，这个问题无法得到解答。"

#: src/usecases.md:108
msgid ""
"In particular when using C family languages, hidden dependencies on header "
"files are easy to miss. For this reason limiting the visibility of files to "
"the compiler by sandboxing is pretty much a requirement for reproducible "
"builds."
msgstr ""
"尤其在使用 C 系语言时，对头文件的隐式依赖很容易被忽略。因此，通过沙箱化来限制"
"编译器可见的文件范围，几乎是实现可复现构建的必要条件。"

#: src/usecases.md:112
msgid ""
"With Josh, each deliverable gets its own virtual git repository with "
"dependencies declared in the `workspace.josh` file. This means answering the "
"above question becomes as simple as comparing commit ids. Furthermore due to "
"the tree filtering each build is guaranteed to be perfectly sandboxed and "
"only sees those parts of the monorepo that have actually been mapped."
msgstr ""
"使用 Josh 时，每个交付物都拥有其独立的虚拟 git 仓库，依赖项在 `workspace.josh` "
"文件中声明。这意味着回答上述问题就如同比较提交 ID 一样简单。此外，由于采用了"
"目录树过滤，每次构建都能保证在完美的沙箱中运行，仅能访问 monorepo 中实际映射"
"的那些部分。"

#: src/usecases.md:117
msgid ""
"This also means the deliverables to be re-built can be determined without "
"cloning any repos like typically necessary with normal build tools."
msgstr ""
"这也意味着无需像普通构建工具通常所要求的那样克隆任何仓库，即可确定需要重新"
"构建的交付物。"

#: src/usecases.md:120 src/reference/graphql.md:1
msgid "GraphQL API"
msgstr "GraphQL API"

#: src/usecases.md:122
msgid ""
"It is often desireable to access content stored in git without requiring a "
"clone of the repository. This is useful for CI/CD systems or web frontends "
"such as dashboards."
msgstr ""
"通常需要在不克隆仓库的情况下访问存储在 git 中的内容，这对于 CI/CD 系统或"
"诸如仪表板之类的 Web 前端非常有用。"

#: src/usecases.md:125
msgid ""
"Josh exposes a GraphQL API for that purpose. For example, it can be used to "
"find all workspaces currently present in the tree:"
msgstr ""
"Josh 为此暴露了一个 GraphQL API。例如，可以用它来查找当前目录树中存在的所有"
"workspace："

#: src/usecases.md:128
msgid ""
"```\n"
"query {\n"
"  rev(at:\"refs/heads/master\", filter:\"::**/workspace.josh\") {\n"
"    files { path }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"query {\n"
"  rev(at:\"refs/heads/master\", filter:\"::**/workspace.josh\") {\n"
"    files { path }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```"

#: src/usecases.md:136
msgid "Caching proxy"
msgstr "缓存代理"

#: src/usecases.md:138
msgid ""
"Even without using the more advanced features like partial cloning or "
"workspaces, `josh-proxy` can act as a cache to reduce traffic between "
"locations or keep your CI from performing many requests to the main git host."
msgstr ""
"即使不使用部分克隆或 workspace 等更高级的功能，`josh-proxy` 也可以充当缓存，"
"以减少各地点之间的流量，或防止 CI 向主 git 主机发起大量请求。"

#: src/faq.md:1
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr "常见问题"

#: src/faq.md:3
msgid "How is Josh different from git sparse-checkout?"
msgstr "Josh 与 git sparse-checkout 有何不同？"

#: src/faq.md:5
msgid ""
"Josh operates on the git object graph and is unrelated to checking out files "
"and the working tree on the filesystem, which is the only thing sparse-"
"checkout is concerned with. A sparse checkout does not influence the "
"contents of the object database and also not what gets downloaded over the "
"network. Both can certainly be used together if needed."
msgstr ""
"Josh 基于 git 对象图，与在文件系统上检出文件和工作树（即 sparse-checkout 的关"
"注点）无关。稀疏检出不会改变对象数据库的内容，也不会影响通过网络下载的内容。两"
"者在需要时可以一起使用。"

#: src/faq.md:8
msgid "How is Josh different from partial clone?"
msgstr "Josh 与部分克隆有何不同？"

#: src/faq.md:10
msgid ""
"A partial clone will cause git to download only parts of an object database "
"according to some predicate. It is still the same object database with the "
"history having the same commits and sha1s. It still allows loading skipped "
"parts of the object database at a later point. Josh creates an alternate "
"history that has no reference to the skipped parts. It is as such very "
"similar to git filter-branch just faster, with added features and a "
"different user interface."
msgstr ""
"部分克隆（partial clone）会根据条件只下载对象数据库的一部分。它仍然是同一个对"
"象数据库：历史包含相同的提交及相同的 SHA-1 标识，并且允许以后再加载此前被跳过"
"的对象。Josh 则会创建一个不引用被跳过部分的替代历史，在本质上类似于 git filter-"
"branch，但更快、功能更多、且提供不同的交互方式。"

#: src/faq.md:13
msgid "How is it different from submodules?"
msgstr "Josh 与子模块有何不同？"

#: src/faq.md:15
msgid ""
"Where git submodules are multiple, independent repos, referencing each other "
"with SHAs, Josh supports the monorepo approach. All of the code is in one "
"single repo which can easily be kept in sync, and Josh provides any sub "
"folder (or in the case of workspaces, more complicated recombination of "
"folders) as their own git repository. These repos are transparently "
"synchronised both ways with the main monorepo. Josh can thus do more than "
"submodules can, and is easier and faster to use."
msgstr ""
"git 子模块（submodules）是多个独立仓库，通过引用特定提交的 SHA 来相互关联。"
"Josh 支持 monorepo（单体仓库）方式：所有代码保存在同一仓库中，便于同步。Josh "
"可以将任意子文件夹（或工作区下更复杂的文件夹组合）视为独立的 git 仓库，与主 "
"monorepo 之间实现双向透明的同步。因此 Josh 的功能超出子模块，且使用上更简单、"
"更快捷。"

#: src/faq.md:20
msgid "How is it different from `git subtree`?"
msgstr "Josh 与 `git subtree` 有何不同？"

#: src/faq.md:22
msgid ""
"The basic idea behind Josh is quite similar to `git subtree`. However `git "
"subtree`, just like `git filter-branch`, is way too slow for everyday use, "
"even on medium sized repos. `git subtree` can only achieve acceptable "
"performance when squashing commits and therefore losing history. One core "
"part of Josh is essentially a much faster implementation of `git subtree "
"split` which has been specifically optimized for being run frequently inside "
"the same repository."
msgstr ""
"Josh 的基本思想与 `git subtree` 相似。然而与 `git filter-branch` 一样，`git "
"subtree` 在常规使用中通常过慢，即便是中等规模的仓库也如此。`git subtree` 只有"
"在压缩提交并因此丢失历史时才可能获得可接受的性能。Josh 的核心本质上是对 `git "
"subtree split` 的高性能实现，针对在同一仓库内频繁运行进行了专门优化。"

#: src/faq.md:27
msgid "How is Josh different from `git filter-repo`?"
msgstr "Josh 与 `git filter-repo` 有何不同？"

#: src/faq.md:29
msgid ""
"Both  `josh-filter` as well as `git filter-repo` enable very fast rewriting "
"of Git history and thus can in simple cases be used for the same purpose."
msgstr ""
"`josh-filter` 和 `git filter-repo` 都能快速重写 Git 历史，在简单场景下可实现相"
"同目的。"

#: src/faq.md:32
msgid ""
"Which one is right in more advanced use cases depends on your goals: `git "
"filter-repo` offers more flexibility and options on what kind of filtering "
"it supports, like rewriting commit messages or even plugging arbitrary "
"scripts into the filtering."
msgstr ""
"在更复杂的用例中，应根据目标选择工具：`git filter-repo` 在过滤能力上更灵活、可"
"选项更多，例如支持重写提交信息或插入任意脚本作为过滤步骤。"

#: src/faq.md:35
msgid ""
"Josh uses a DSL instead of arbitrary scripts for complex filters and is much "
"more restrictive in the kind of filtering possible, but in exchange for "
"those limitations offers incremental filtering as well as bidirectional "
"operation, meaning converting changes between both the original and the "
"filtered repos."
msgstr ""
"Josh 使用 DSL（领域特定语言）而非任意脚本，因此在可实现的过滤类型上更受限制；"
"但它支持增量过滤和双向操作，能够在原始仓库与过滤后仓库之间相互转换变更。"

#: src/faq.md:38
msgid "How is Josh different from all of the above alternatives?"
msgstr "Josh 与以上所有替代方案有何不同？"

#: src/faq.md:40
msgid ""
"Josh includes `josh-proxy` which offers repo filtering as a service, mainly "
"intended to support monorepo workflows."
msgstr ""
"Josh 包含 `josh-proxy`，以服务形式提供仓库过滤，主要用于支持 monorepo 工作流。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:1
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr "快速入门"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:3
msgid ""
"The `josh` command-line tool lets you clone, fetch, push, and manage "
"filtered views of git repositories directly from your terminal."
msgstr ""
"`josh` 命令行工具让您可以直接在终端中克隆、fetch、push 以及管理 git 仓库的"
"过滤视图。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:6 src/reference/cli.md:6
msgid "Installation"
msgstr "安装"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:8
msgid "Install `josh` using Cargo (requires [Rust](https://rustup.rs)):"
msgstr "使用 Cargo 安装 `josh`（需要 [Rust](https://rustup.rs)）："

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:10 src/reference/cli.md:8
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"cargo install josh-cli --locked --git https://github.com/josh-project/josh."
"git\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"cargo install josh-cli --locked --git https://github.com/josh-project/josh."
"git\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:14
msgid "Cloning a repository"
msgstr "克隆仓库"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:16
msgid ""
"`josh clone` is similar to `git clone` but takes two required arguments "
"after the URL: a [filter](../reference/filters.md) and a local destination "
"path. Unlike `git clone`, the destination path is always required and cannot "
"be inferred from the URL."
msgstr ""
"`josh clone` 与 `git clone` 类似，但在 URL 之后需要两个必填参数："
"一个[过滤器](../reference/filters.md)和一个本地目标路径。与 `git clone` 不同，"
"目标路径始终是必须的，无法从 URL 中推断。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:20
msgid ""
"For example, let's clone just the documentation folder of the Josh "
"repository:"
msgstr "例如，仅克隆 Josh 仓库的文档目录："

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:22
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/josh-project/josh.git :/docs ./josh-docs\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/josh-project/josh.git :/docs ./josh-docs\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:26
msgid ""
"The filter `:/docs` tells Josh to check out only the contents of the `docs/` "
"subdirectory. The resulting repository will contain only the files from that "
"folder and only the commits that touch them — as if that subdirectory had "
"always been its own repository."
msgstr ""
"过滤器 `:/docs` 指示 Josh 仅签出 `docs/` 子目录的内容。生成的仓库将只包含该"
"目录中的文件，以及仅触及这些文件的提交——就好像该子目录一直是其独立的仓库一样。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:30
msgid ""
"To clone a repository without any filter (equivalent to a plain `git clone`):"
msgstr "要在不使用任何过滤器的情况下克隆仓库（等同于普通的 `git clone`）："

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:32
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/josh-project/josh.git :/ ./josh\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/josh-project/josh.git :/ ./josh\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:36
msgid "Making and pushing changes"
msgstr "修改并推送变更"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:38
msgid ""
"The cloned repository is a normal git repository. Edit files, commit as "
"usual, then use `josh push` to send your changes back upstream:"
msgstr ""
"克隆出来的仓库是一个普通 git 仓库。像平常一样编辑文件并提交，然后使用 `josh "
"push` 将你的变更发送回上游："

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:47
msgid ""
"Josh transparently reverses the filter and applies your commits to the "
"correct location in the upstream repository. From the perspective of the "
"rest of the team, the changes appear exactly as if they had been pushed "
"directly to the monorepo."
msgstr ""
"Josh 会透明地反向应用过滤器，并将你的提交应用到上游仓库中的正确位置。从团队"
"其他成员的视角看，这些变更就像是直接推送到 monorepo 一样。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:51
msgid "Pulling changes"
msgstr "拉取变更"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:53
msgid "Use `josh pull` to fetch and integrate updates from upstream:"
msgstr "使用 `josh pull` 从上游获取并集成更新："

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:59
msgid "Cloning a part of a repository"
msgstr "克隆仓库的一部分"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:61
msgid ""
"Josh becomes particularly useful when you want to work on a filtered view of "
"a larger repository — for example, a single subdirectory or a composed "
"workspace. The `josh` CLI applies the filter client-side, which means the "
"full repository object database is still downloaded from the upstream host. "
"The filter determines which commits and files are visible in your working "
"tree and which refs you can push to, but it does not reduce transfer size."
msgstr ""
"当你想在大型仓库的过滤视图上工作时，Josh 会特别有用，例如单个子目录或组合后"
"的 workspace。`josh` CLI 会在客户端应用过滤器，这意味着仍然会从上游主机下载"
"完整的仓库对象数据库。过滤器决定哪些提交和文件会在工作树中可见，以及你可以"
"推送到哪些 ref，但它不会减少传输大小。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:68
msgid ""
"**Note**: If a true partial download is important — for example to avoid "
"transferring a large monorepo over a slow connection — you need server-side "
"filtering via a [josh-proxy](../reference/proxy.md). With the proxy in "
"place, only the filtered objects are ever sent over the network."
msgstr ""
"**注意**：如果真正的部分下载很重要，例如为了避免在慢速连接上传输大型 monorepo，"
"你需要通过 [josh-proxy](../reference/proxy.md) 进行服务端过滤。部署代理后，"
"网络上传输的始终只有过滤后的对象。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:73
msgid ""
"Beyond simple subdirectory extraction, Josh's [filter language](../reference/"
"filters.md) supports composition, remapping, and exclusions, making it "
"possible to carve out any virtual slice of a repository."
msgstr ""
"除了简单的子目录提取之外，Josh 的[过滤器语言](../reference/filters.md)还支持"
"组合、重映射和排除，从而可以切分出仓库中的任意虚拟片段。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:77
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr "后续步骤"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:79
msgid ""
"**[Workspaces](./workspaces.md)** — Compose a virtual repository from "
"multiple parts of a monorepo and keep them in sync bidirectionally."
msgstr ""
"**[Workspaces](./workspaces.md)** — 从 monorepo 的多个部分组合出一个虚拟仓库，"
"并保持双向同步。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:81
msgid ""
"**[Stacked changes](./stacked-changes.md)** — Push a series of commits as "
"individual pull requests with automatic PR management."
msgstr ""
"**[Stacked changes](./stacked-changes.md)** — 将一系列提交推送为单独的 pull "
"request，并自动管理 PR。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:83
msgid ""
"**[Filter syntax](../reference/filters.md)** — Learn all the available "
"filter operations."
msgstr "**[Filter syntax](../reference/filters.md)** — 了解所有可用的过滤器操作。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:85
msgid ""
"**[josh CLI reference](../reference/cli.md)** — Full reference for all "
"`josh` subcommands and options."
msgstr ""
"**[josh CLI reference](../reference/cli.md)** — 所有 `josh` 子命令和选项的完整"
"参考。"

#: src/guide/gettingstarted.md:87
msgid ""
"**[Proxy setup](../reference/proxy.md)** — Running a shared `josh-proxy` for "
"your team or CI/CD infrastructure, so that ordinary `git clone` works "
"without any special client tooling."
msgstr ""
"**[Proxy setup](../reference/proxy.md)** — 为团队或 CI/CD 基础设施运行共享的 "
"`josh-proxy`，让普通的 `git clone` 无需任何特殊客户端工具即可工作。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:3
msgid ""
"A workspace is a list of files and folders remapped from a central "
"repository into a new repository layout. For example, a shared library can "
"be mapped into multiple workspaces, each placing it at the path that makes "
"sense for that project."
msgstr ""
"workspace 是一组文件和文件夹的列表，它们会从中心仓库重映射到新的仓库布局中。"
"例如，一个共享库可以映射到多个 workspace 中，并在每个 workspace 中放到对该"
"项目有意义的路径下。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:7
msgid ""
"In this guide we'll set up a small monorepo with two libraries and two "
"applications, then use workspaces to develop against them in isolation."
msgstr ""
"在本指南中，我们会设置一个包含两个库和两个应用的小型 monorepo，然后使用 "
"workspace 对它们进行隔离开发。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:10
msgid "The monorepo"
msgstr "Monorepo"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:12
msgid "Suppose you have a monorepo with this structure:"
msgstr "假设你有一个结构如下的 monorepo："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:26
msgid ""
"Both applications depend on one or both of the shared libraries, but "
"developers working on each application only want to see the code that's "
"relevant to them."
msgstr ""
"两个应用都依赖其中一个或两个共享库，但开发每个应用的开发者只想看到与自己相关"
"的代码。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:29
msgid "Creating a workspace"
msgstr "创建 workspace"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:31
msgid ""
"Clone the monorepo scoped to `application1` using the `:workspace=` filter:"
msgstr "使用 `:workspace=` 过滤器克隆范围限定为 `application1` 的 monorepo："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:33
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/myorg/monorepo.git :workspace=application1 ./"
"application1\n"
"cd application1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/myorg/monorepo.git :workspace=application1 ./"
"application1\n"
"cd application1\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:38
msgid ""
"The cloned repository contains only the files and history relevant to "
"`application1`:"
msgstr "克隆得到的仓库只包含与 `application1` 相关的文件和历史："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:44
msgid ""
"**Note:** Josh lets you create a workspace out of any directory, even one "
"that doesn't exist yet in the monorepo."
msgstr ""
"**注意：** Josh 允许你基于任意目录创建 workspace，即使该目录在 monorepo 中还"
"不存在。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:47
msgid "Mapping dependencies with `workspace.josh`"
msgstr "使用 `workspace.josh` 映射依赖"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:49
msgid ""
"The `workspace.josh` file describes which folders from the central "
"repository should be mapped into this workspace, and where they should "
"appear."
msgstr ""
"`workspace.josh` 文件描述中心仓库中的哪些文件夹应映射到此 workspace，以及它们"
"应出现在哪个位置。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:52
msgid ""
"Since `application1` depends on `library1`, create `workspace.josh` with:"
msgstr "由于 `application1` 依赖 `library1`，请创建包含以下内容的 `workspace.josh`："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:58
msgid "Commit the file:"
msgstr "提交该文件："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:60
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"git add workspace.josh\n"
"git commit -m \"Map library1 into the application1 workspace\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"git add workspace.josh\n"
"git commit -m \"Map library1 into the application1 workspace\"\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:65
msgid "Then push and pull to sync the workspace:"
msgstr "然后推送并拉取，以同步 workspace："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:72
msgid "The mapped library has now appeared in the workspace:"
msgstr "映射后的库现在已经出现在 workspace 中："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:82
msgid ""
"The history reflects the merge of `library1`'s history into the workspace:"
msgstr "历史记录反映出 `library1` 的历史已合并到 workspace 中："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:91
msgid ""
"Josh needs to merge the mapped module's history into the workspace so that "
"all commits are present in both histories. In the central repository, the "
"same commit appears as a plain linear commit — no merge — in `application1/`:"
msgstr ""
"Josh 需要将映射模块的历史合并到 workspace 中，以便所有提交同时存在于两边的"
"历史中。在中心仓库里，同一个提交会在 `application1/` 中显示为普通的线性提交"
"——没有 merge："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:104
msgid "A second workspace"
msgstr "第二个 workspace"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:106
msgid ""
"Let's create a workspace for `application2`, which depends on both libraries:"
msgstr "接下来为依赖两个库的 `application2` 创建一个 workspace："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:108
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"cd ..\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/myorg/monorepo.git :workspace=application2 ./"
"application2\n"
"cd application2\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"cd ..\n"
"josh clone https://github.com/myorg/monorepo.git :workspace=application2 ./"
"application2\n"
"cd application2\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:114
msgid "Add both dependencies to `workspace.josh`:"
msgstr "将两个依赖都添加到 `workspace.josh`："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:121
msgid "Commit, push, and pull:"
msgstr "提交、推送并拉取："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:123
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"git add workspace.josh\n"
"git commit -m \"Create workspace for application2\"\n"
"josh push\n"
"josh pull\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"git add workspace.josh\n"
"git commit -m \"Create workspace for application2\"\n"
"josh push\n"
"josh pull\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:130
msgid "The workspace now contains both libraries:"
msgstr "该 workspace 现在包含两个库："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:142
msgid ""
"Because we added both dependencies in a single commit, the history contains "
"just one merge commit, pulling in the history of both libraries:"
msgstr ""
"由于我们在单个提交中添加了两个依赖，历史记录只包含一个 merge commit，它引入了"
"两个库的历史："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:153
msgid "Pushing a change back to the monorepo"
msgstr "将变更推回 monorepo"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:155
msgid ""
"While working in `application2`, you notice a bug in `library1`. Fix it and "
"commit as usual:"
msgstr "在 `application2` 中工作时，你发现 `library1` 中有一个 bug。修复它并照常提交："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:158
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"# edit libs/lib1/lib1.h\n"
"git commit -a -m \"Fix bug in lib1\"\n"
"josh push\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```shell\n"
"# edit libs/lib1/lib1.h\n"
"git commit -a -m \"Fix bug in lib1\"\n"
"josh push\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:164
msgid ""
"Josh reverses the workspace filter and writes the change directly to "
"`library1/` in the central repository. No special tooling is needed — it's a "
"regular commit from the perspective of everyone else working on the monorepo."
msgstr ""
"Josh 会反向应用 workspace 过滤器，并将变更直接写入中心仓库的 `library1/`。"
"不需要特殊工具——从其他所有在 monorepo 上工作的人的视角看，它就是一个普通提交。"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:168
msgid "Pulling a change from another workspace"
msgstr "从另一个 workspace 拉取变更"

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:170
msgid "A developer working in `application1` can now pull the fix:"
msgstr "在 `application1` 中工作的开发者现在可以拉取该修复："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:177
msgid ""
"The fix appears in `modules/lib1/` exactly as if it had been committed there "
"directly:"
msgstr "该修复会出现在 `modules/lib1/` 中，就像它是直接提交到那里的一样："

#: src/guide/workspaces.md:187
msgid ""
"Changes flow bidirectionally through the central repository — each workspace "
"is an isolated view, but they all share the same underlying history."
msgstr ""
"变更会通过中心仓库双向流动——每个 workspace 都是一个隔离视图，但它们共享同一套"
"底层历史。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:1
msgid "Stacked Changes"
msgstr "堆叠式变更"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:3
msgid ""
"Josh supports a stacked-changes workflow where a series of commits on a "
"local branch can each be pushed as a separate, independently-reviewable "
"unit. This is useful when working on a larger feature that is best reviewed "
"in smaller, logical steps."
msgstr ""
"Josh 支持堆叠式变更工作流：本地分支上的一系列提交可以分别作为独立、可单独审查"
"的单元推送。当开发较大的功能，并且最好拆成较小的逻辑步骤来审查时，这会很有用。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:7
msgid ""
"This feature is separate from Josh's filtering functionality. It works with "
"any repository accessible via the `josh` CLI, regardless of whether you are "
"working with a filtered view of a monorepo or a plain repository."
msgstr ""
"此功能独立于 Josh 的过滤功能。它适用于任何可通过 `josh` CLI 访问的仓库，无论"
"你是在 monorepo 的过滤视图中工作，还是在普通仓库中工作。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:11
msgid "Concepts"
msgstr "概念"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:13
msgid ""
"In a stacked changes workflow, each commit on your local branch represents "
"one self-contained change. When you use `josh publish`, Josh creates a "
"separate git ref for each qualifying commit."
msgstr ""
"在堆叠式变更工作流中，本地分支上的每个提交都表示一个自包含的变更。使用 `josh "
"publish` 时，Josh 会为每个符合条件的提交创建单独的 git ref。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:17
msgid ""
"A commit qualifies for a separate ref — and an automatic PR, when [forge "
"integration](../reference/forge.md) is configured — only if both of the "
"following are true:"
msgstr ""
"只有在同时满足以下两个条件时，提交才有资格获得单独的 ref；如果配置了[代码托管"
"平台集成](../reference/forge.md)，还会自动创建 PR："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:21
msgid "**It has a change ID** in the commit message footer (see below)."
msgstr "**它在提交消息页脚中包含 change ID**（见下文）。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:22
msgid ""
"**Its author email matches** the email configured in `user.email` in your "
"git config."
msgstr "**它的作者邮箱匹配** git config 中 `user.email` 配置的邮箱。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:24
msgid ""
"Commits without a change ID, or authored by someone else, are silently "
"skipped and are not pushed as individual changes."
msgstr ""
"没有 change ID 的提交，或由其他人创作的提交，会被静默跳过，不会作为单独变更"
"推送。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:27
msgid "Change IDs"
msgstr "Change ID"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:29
msgid ""
"A change ID is a short, stable identifier that you add manually to the "
"footer of a commit message, using either of these footers:"
msgstr ""
"change ID 是一个简短、稳定的标识符，需要你手动添加到提交消息的页脚中，可以"
"使用以下任一页脚："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:36
msgid "or the Gerrit-compatible form:"
msgstr "或使用兼容 Gerrit 的形式："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:42
msgid ""
"The change ID must not contain `@`. It must be unique within the stack. It "
"is what allows `josh push` to match a commit to an existing PR across "
"rebases and amends — so once you have assigned an ID to a change, keep it "
"stable."
msgstr ""
"change ID 不能包含 `@`。它必须在堆栈内唯一。它让 `josh push` 能够在 rebase 和"
" amend 之后仍将提交匹配到已有 PR；因此一旦为某个变更分配了 ID，就要保持它稳定。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:46
msgid "**Example commit message:**"
msgstr "**示例提交消息：**"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:57
msgid "Declaring dependencies with `Requires:`"
msgstr "使用 `Requires:` 声明依赖"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:59
msgid ""
"By default, when Josh publishes a stack it includes only the intermediate "
"commits that are textually needed for a change's diff to apply. Sometimes a "
"change depends on another change in ways that go beyond textual conflicts — "
"for example, it relies on a function introduced by an earlier change even "
"though they touch different files."
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，Josh 发布一个堆栈时，只会包含应用某个变更 diff 在文本上所需的中间"
"提交。有时，一个变更会以超出文本冲突的方式依赖另一个变更；例如，它依赖前一个"
"变更引入的函数，即使两个变更触及的是不同文件。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:64
msgid ""
"You can declare such dependencies with one or more `Requires:` footers in "
"the commit message, referencing the change IDs of the changes you depend on:"
msgstr ""
"你可以在提交消息中使用一个或多个 `Requires:` 页脚声明这类依赖，引用所依赖变更"
"的 change ID："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:77
msgid ""
"When Josh determines the dependencies for `form-wiring`, it will include "
"`input-validation` even if the two changes don't overlap textually."
msgstr ""
"当 Josh 确定 `form-wiring` 的依赖时，即使这两个变更在文本上没有重叠，也会包含 "
"`input-validation`。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:80
msgid "Multiple dependencies can be declared by repeating the footer:"
msgstr "可以通过重复该页脚来声明多个依赖："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:88
msgid ""
"If a `Requires:` references a change ID that does not exist in the current "
"stack, it is silently ignored. This commonly happens when the required "
"change has already been merged into the base branch — the dependency is "
"satisfied by the base itself, so there is nothing extra to include."
msgstr ""
"如果 `Requires:` 引用了当前堆栈中不存在的 change ID，它会被静默忽略。这通常"
"发生在所需变更已经合入 base 分支时——依赖已经由 base 本身满足，因此没有额外"
"内容需要包含。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:93
msgid "Workflow"
msgstr "工作流"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:95
msgid "1. Write your commits"
msgstr "1. 编写提交"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:97
msgid ""
"Work on your feature normally, writing one commit per logical step. Add a "
"`Change:` footer to each commit you want to submit for review:"
msgstr ""
"像平常一样开发功能，每个逻辑步骤编写一个提交。为每个想提交审查的提交添加 "
"`Change:` 页脚："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:100
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ git commit -m \"Add validation for input fields\n"
"\n"
"Change: input-validation\"\n"
"\n"
"$ git commit -m \"Wire validation into the form component\n"
"\n"
"Change: form-wiring\"\n"
"\n"
"$ git commit -m \"Add tests for form validation\n"
"\n"
"Change: validation-tests\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"$ git commit -m \"Add validation for input fields\n"
"\n"
"Change: input-validation\"\n"
"\n"
"$ git commit -m \"Wire validation into the form component\n"
"\n"
"Change: form-wiring\"\n"
"\n"
"$ git commit -m \"Add tests for form validation\n"
"\n"
"Change: validation-tests\"\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:114
msgid ""
"Commits without a `Change:` footer are included in the push to the base "
"branch but do not get their own ref or PR."
msgstr ""
"没有 `Change:` 页脚的提交会包含在推送到 base 分支的内容中，但不会获得自己的 "
"ref 或 PR。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:117
msgid "2. Publish"
msgstr "2. 发布"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:123
msgid ""
"For each qualifying commit Josh pushes a ref under `refs/heads/@changes/"
"<base>/<author>/<change-id>`. With GitHub forge integration enabled, a pull "
"request is created (or updated) for each of these refs automatically."
msgstr ""
"对于每个符合条件的提交，Josh 会在 `refs/heads/@changes/<base>/<author>/"
"<change-id>` 下推送一个 ref。启用 GitHub 代码托管平台集成后，每个 ref 都会"
"自动创建（或更新）一个 pull request。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:127
msgid ""
"The first change in the stack targets the repository's default branch. Each "
"subsequent PR targets the branch of the change before it. Intermediate PRs "
"are automatically marked as **draft** until the changes before them are "
"merged."
msgstr ""
"堆栈中的第一个变更以仓库的默认分支为目标。之后的每个 PR 都以前一个变更的分支"
"为目标。中间 PR 会自动标记为 **draft**，直到位于它们之前的变更被合并。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:131
msgid "3. Iterate"
msgstr "3. 迭代"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:133
msgid ""
"After receiving review feedback, amend or rebase your commits as needed, "
"keeping the `Change:` footers intact:"
msgstr "收到审查反馈后，按需 amend 或 rebase 你的提交，并保持 `Change:` 页脚不变："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:141
msgid ""
"As long as the change ID in the footer is preserved through your edits, "
"`josh publish` updates the correct existing PRs rather than creating new "
"ones."
msgstr ""
"只要编辑过程中保留页脚中的 change ID，`josh publish` 就会更新正确的现有 PR，"
"而不是创建新的 PR。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:144
msgid "4. Merge"
msgstr "4. 合并"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:146
msgid ""
"Once a PR is approved and its required checks pass, merge it through the "
"forge's normal UI. Then sync your local branch to account for the merged "
"commit:"
msgstr ""
"PR 获得批准且其必需检查通过后，通过代码托管平台的常规 UI 合并它。然后同步你的"
"本地分支，以纳入已合并的提交："

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:153
msgid ""
"This rebases your remaining local commits on top of the updated upstream "
"state. `--autostash` ensures any uncommitted changes are preserved across "
"the operation. After pulling, the next `josh publish` will retarget and "
"promote the next PR in the stack from draft to ready for review."
msgstr ""
"这会将你剩余的本地提交 rebase 到更新后的上游状态之上。`--autostash` 可确保"
"未提交的变更在整个操作过程中得到保留。拉取后，下一次 `josh publish` 会重新"
"确定目标，并将堆栈中的下一个 PR 从 draft 提升为可供审查。"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:158
msgid "Without forge integration"
msgstr "没有代码托管平台集成时"

#: src/guide/stacked-changes.md:160
msgid ""
"`josh publish` works without [forge integration](../reference/forge.md). "
"Josh still pushes the individual `@changes/…` refs to the upstream "
"repository; you can then create pull requests from them manually, or use "
"them as part of a custom review workflow."
msgstr ""
"`josh publish` 无需[代码托管平台集成](../reference/forge.md)也能工作。Josh "
"仍会将各个 `@changes/…` ref 推送到上游仓库；随后你可以手动从它们创建 pull "
"request，或将它们用作自定义审查工作流的一部分。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:3
msgid ""
"When moving to a monorepo setup, especially in existing organisations, it is "
"common that the need to consolidate existing project repositories arises."
msgstr ""
"迁移到 monorepo 设置时，尤其是在已有组织中，经常会出现整合现有项目仓库的需求。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:7
msgid ""
"The simplest possible case is one where the previous history of a project "
"does not need to be retained. In this case, the projects files can simply be "
"copied into the monoreop at the appropriate location and committed."
msgstr ""
"最简单的情况是无需保留项目之前的历史。在这种情况下，可以直接将项目文件复制到 "
"monorepo 中的适当位置并提交。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:12
msgid ""
"If history should be retained, josh can be used for importing a project as "
"an alternative to built-in git commands like [`git subtree`](https://"
"manpages.debian.org/testing/git-man/git-subtree.1.en.html)."
msgstr ""
"如果需要保留历史，可以使用 josh 导入项目，作为 [`git subtree`](https://"
"manpages.debian.org/testing/git-man/git-subtree.1.en.html) 等 git 内置命令的"
"替代方案。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:16
msgid ""
"Josh's [filter capability](../reference/filters.md) lets you perform "
"transformations on the history of a git repository to arbitrarily "
"(re-)compose paths inside of a repository."
msgstr ""
"Josh 的[过滤能力](../reference/filters.md)允许你对 git 仓库历史执行转换，从而"
"任意（重新）组合仓库内部的路径。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:20
msgid ""
"A key aspect of this functionality is that all transformations are "
"_reversible_. This means that if you apply a transformation moving files "
"from the root of a repository to, say, `tools/project-b`, followed by an "
"_inverse_ transformation moving files from `tools/project-b` back to the "
"root, you receive the same commit hashes you put in."
msgstr ""
"此功能的一个关键点是所有转换都是_可逆的_。这意味着，如果你先应用一个转换，将"
"文件从仓库根目录移动到例如 `tools/project-b`，然后再应用一个_反向_转换，将文件"
"从 `tools/project-b` 移回根目录，最终得到的提交哈希会与输入时相同。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:27
msgid ""
"We can use this feature to import a project into our monorepo while allowing "
"external users to keep pulling on top of the same git history they already "
"have, just with a new git remote."
msgstr ""
"我们可以利用这个功能将项目导入 monorepo，同时允许外部用户继续基于他们已有的"
"同一份 git 历史拉取更新，只是改用一个新的 git remote。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:31
msgid ""
"There are multiple ways of doing this, with the most common ones outlined "
"below. You can look at [`josh#596`](https://github.com/josh-project/josh/"
"issues/596) for a discussion of several other methods."
msgstr ""
"实现这一点有多种方式，下面概述了最常见的几种。你可以查看 [`josh#596`](https://"
"github.com/josh-project/josh/issues/596)，其中讨论了其他几种方法。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:35
msgid "Import with `josh-filter`"
msgstr "使用 `josh-filter` 导入"

#: src/guide/importing.md:37
msgid ""
"Currently, the easiest way to do this is by using the `josh-filter` binary "
"which is a command-line frontend to josh's filter capabilities."
msgstr ""
"目前，最简单的方法是使用 `josh-filter` 二进制文件，它是 josh 过滤能力的命令行"
"前端。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:40
msgid "Inside of our target repository, it would work like this:"
msgstr "在目标仓库内部，其工作方式如下："

#: src/guide/importing.md:42
msgid ""
"Fetch the repository we want to import (say, \"Project B\", from "
"`$REPO_URL`)."
msgstr "获取我们想导入的仓库（比如从 `$REPO_URL` 获取 \"Project B\"）。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:49
msgid "This will set the `FETCH_HEAD` reference to the fetched repository."
msgstr "这会将 `FETCH_HEAD` 引用设置为获取到的仓库。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:51
msgid ""
"Rewrite the history of that repository through josh to make it look as if "
"the project had always been developed at our target path (say, `tools/"
"project-b`)."
msgstr ""
"通过 josh 重写该仓库的历史，使其看起来就像该项目一直是在目标路径（比如 "
"`tools/project-b`）下开发的一样。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:57
msgid "':prefix=tools/project-b'"
msgstr "':prefix=tools/project-b'"

#: src/guide/importing.md:60
msgid "This will set the `FILTERED_HEAD` reference to the rewritten history."
msgstr "这会将 `FILTERED_HEAD` 引用设置为重写后的历史。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:63
msgid "Merge the rewritten history into our target repository."
msgstr "将重写后的历史合并到目标仓库中。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:69
msgid ""
"After this merge commit, the previously external project now lives at `tools/"
"project-b` as expected."
msgstr "在这个 merge commit 之后，之前的外部项目现在会按预期位于 `tools/project-b`。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:72
msgid ""
"Any external users can now use the `:/tools/project-b` josh filter to "
"retrieve changes made in the new project location - without the git hashes "
"of their existing commits changing (that is to say, without conflicting)."
msgstr ""
"任何外部用户现在都可以使用 `:/tools/project-b` josh 过滤器来获取新项目位置中的"
"变更，而不会改变他们现有提交的 git 哈希（也就是说，不会产生冲突）。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:77
msgid "Import by pushing to josh"
msgstr "通过推送到 josh 导入"

#: src/guide/importing.md:79
msgid ""
"If your monorepo is already running a `josh-proxy` in front of it, you can "
"also import a project by pushing a project merge to josh."
msgstr ""
"如果你的 monorepo 前面已经运行了 `josh-proxy`，也可以通过向 josh 推送项目合并"
"来导入项目。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:82
msgid ""
"This has the benefit of not needing to clone the entire monorepo locally to "
"do a merge, but the drawback of using a different, slightly slower filter "
"mechanism when exporting the tree back out. For projects with very large "
"history, consider using the `josh-filter` mechanism outlined above."
msgstr ""
"这样做的好处是不需要在本地克隆整个 monorepo 来执行合并，但缺点是在重新导出树"
"时会使用另一种稍慢的过滤机制。对于历史非常庞大的项目，请考虑使用上面概述的 "
"`josh-filter` 机制。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:88
msgid "Pushing a project merge to josh works like this:"
msgstr "向 josh 推送项目合并的方式如下："

#: src/guide/importing.md:90
msgid ""
"Assume we have a local checkout of \"Project B\", and we want to merge this "
"into our monorepo. There is a `josh-proxy` running at `https://git.company."
"name/monorepo.git`. We want to merge this project into `/tools/project-b` in "
"the monorepo."
msgstr ""
"假设我们有 \"Project B\" 的本地 checkout，并且想将其合并到 monorepo 中。有一个 "
"`josh-proxy` 正运行在 `https://git.company.name/monorepo.git`。我们想将该项目"
"合并到 monorepo 中的 `/tools/project-b`。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:95
msgid "In the checkout of \"Project B\", add the josh remote:"
msgstr "在 \"Project B\" 的 checkout 中，添加 josh remote："

#: src/guide/importing.md:101
msgid ""
"Note the use of the `/tools/project-b.git` josh filter, which points to a "
"path that should not yet exist in the monorepo."
msgstr ""
"注意这里使用了 `/tools/project-b.git` josh 过滤器，它指向 monorepo 中尚不应"
"存在的路径。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:104
msgid ""
"Push the repository to josh with the `-o merge` option, creating a merge "
"commit introducing the project history at that location, while retaining its "
"history:"
msgstr ""
"使用 `-o merge` 选项将仓库推送到 josh，创建一个 merge commit，在该位置引入项目"
"历史，同时保留其历史："

#: src/guide/importing.md:112
msgid "Note for Gerrit users"
msgstr "Gerrit 用户注意事项"

#: src/guide/importing.md:114
msgid ""
"With either method, when merging a set of new commits into a Gerrit "
"repository and going through the standard code-review process, Gerrit might "
"complain about missing Change-IDs in the imported commits."
msgstr ""
"无论使用哪种方法，当将一组新提交合并到 Gerrit 仓库并走标准代码审查流程时，"
"Gerrit 可能会抱怨导入的提交缺少 Change-ID。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:118
msgid ""
"To work around this, the commits need to first be made \"known\" to Gerrit. "
"This can be achieved by pushing the new parent of the merge commit to a "
"separate branch in Gerrit directly (without going through the review "
"mechanism). After this Gerrit will accept merge commits referencing that "
"parent, as long as the merge commit itself has a Change-ID."
msgstr ""
"为了解决这个问题，需要先让 Gerrit \"知道\" 这些提交。可以通过将 merge commit "
"的新父提交直接推送到 Gerrit 中的一个单独分支来实现（不经过审查机制）。之后，"
"只要 merge commit 本身带有 Change-ID，Gerrit 就会接受引用该父提交的 merge commit。"

#: src/guide/importing.md:125
msgid ""
"Some monorepo setups on Gerrit use a special unrestricted branch like `merge-"
"staging` for this, to which users with permission to import projects can "
"force-push unrelated histories."
msgstr ""
"Gerrit 上的一些 monorepo 设置会为此使用类似 `merge-staging` 的特殊非受限分支，"
"有项目导入权限的用户可以向该分支 force-push 无关历史。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:3
msgid ""
"This page covers breaking changes introduced in recent releases and how to "
"adapt to them."
msgstr "本页面介绍近期版本中引入的破坏性变更，以及如何适配这些变更。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:5
msgid "CRLF line endings in gpgsig headers preserved"
msgstr "保留 gpgsig 头中的 CRLF 换行符"

#: src/guide/migration.md:7 src/guide/migration.md:28 src/guide/migration.md:50
#: src/guide/migration.md:60 src/guide/migration.md:69
#: src/guide/migration.md:119
msgid "_Applies when upgrading from r24.10.04 to r26.04.19._"
msgstr "_适用于从 r24.10.04 升级到 r26.04.19。_"

#: src/guide/migration.md:9
msgid ""
"Josh previously accidentally normalized `\\r\\n` line endings to `\\n` "
"inside the `gpgsig` header of commit objects. This was a bug — git treats "
"gpgsig values as opaque bytes, and the standard format uses `\\n` throughout "
"— and has been fixed. Josh now preserves whichever line endings are present "
"in the original commit."
msgstr ""
"Josh 之前会意外地将提交对象 `gpgsig` 头中的 `\\r\\n` 换行符规范化为 `\\n`。"
"这是一个 bug——git 会将 gpgsig 值视为不透明字节，而标准格式全程使用 `\\n`——"
"该问题现已修复。Josh 现在会保留原始提交中存在的任何换行符。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:14
msgid ""
"**What changed:** If your upstream history contains commits with `\\r\\n` in "
"their gpgsig headers, the filtered commit hashes will differ from those "
"produced by the old version."
msgstr ""
"**变更内容：** 如果你的上游历史包含 gpgsig 头中带有 `\\r\\n` 的提交，过滤后的"
"提交哈希将不同于旧版本生成的哈希。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:17
msgid ""
"**How to restore the old behavior:** Use the `gpgsig=\"norm-lf\"` meta "
"option if you need to reproduce a history that was created with the old "
"normalization:"
msgstr ""
"**如何恢复旧行为：** 如果需要复现使用旧规范化行为创建的历史，请使用 "
"`gpgsig=\"norm-lf\"` meta 选项："

#: src/guide/migration.md:20
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(gpgsig=\"norm-lf\")[:/your/filter]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(gpgsig=\"norm-lf\")[:/your/filter]\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/migration.md:24
msgid ""
"See the [gpgsig option](../reference/filters.md#gpgsig-option) for details."
msgstr "详情请参见 [gpgsig 选项](../reference/filters.md#gpgsig-option)。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:26
msgid "Trivial merges removed by default"
msgstr "默认移除平凡合并"

#: src/guide/migration.md:30
msgid ""
"Josh previously kept all merge commits in the filtered history, even when "
"the filtered tree of a merge commit was identical to its first parent's tree "
"(a \"trivial merge\"). Trivial merges are now removed by default during "
"history simplification."
msgstr ""
"Josh 之前会在过滤后的历史中保留所有 merge commit，即使某个 merge commit 的过滤"
"后 tree 与其第一个父提交的 tree 完全相同（即 \"trivial merge\"）。现在，在历史"
"简化过程中会默认移除平凡合并。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:34
msgid ""
"**What changed:** Filtered histories produced by the same filter may differ "
"from those produced by older versions of Josh if the upstream history "
"contains trivial merges. The internal cache version has been bumped, so all "
"results will be recomputed on the first run after upgrading."
msgstr ""
"**变更内容：** 如果上游历史包含平凡合并，同一过滤器生成的过滤历史可能不同于"
"旧版本 Josh 生成的结果。内部缓存版本已提升，因此升级后的首次运行会重新计算所有"
"结果。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:39
msgid ""
"**How to restore the old behavior:** Wrap your filter with the "
"`history=\"keep-trivial-merges\"` meta option:"
msgstr ""
"**如何恢复旧行为：** 使用 `history=\"keep-trivial-merges\"` meta 选项包裹你的"
"过滤器："

#: src/guide/migration.md:42
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(history=\"keep-trivial-merges\")[:/your/filter]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(history=\"keep-trivial-merges\")[:/your/filter]\n"
"```"

#: src/guide/migration.md:46
msgid ""
"See [Filter options](../reference/filters.md#history-option) for details."
msgstr "详情请参见[过滤器选项](../reference/filters.md#history-option)。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:48
msgid "`:join` filter removed"
msgstr "移除 `:join` 过滤器"

#: src/guide/migration.md:52
msgid ""
"The `:join` filter has been removed. It was a limited alternative to using "
"`--reverse`/push for reconstructing upstream history from a filtered view."
msgstr ""
"`:join` 过滤器已被移除。它曾是从过滤视图重建上游历史时，替代 `--reverse`/push "
"的一种受限方案。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:55
msgid ""
"**How to migrate:** Use `josh-filter --reverse` or `josh push` to write "
"changes back to the upstream repository."
msgstr "**如何迁移：** 使用 `josh-filter --reverse` 或 `josh push` 将变更写回上游仓库。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:58
msgid "josh-ui (web UI) removed"
msgstr "移除 josh-ui（Web UI）"

#: src/guide/migration.md:62
msgid ""
"The `/ui` endpoint and the `josh-ui` component have been removed from the "
"project."
msgstr "项目中已移除 `/ui` 端点和 `josh-ui` 组件。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:64
msgid ""
"**How to migrate:** There is no direct replacement. Remove any links or "
"integrations that pointed to the `/ui` endpoint."
msgstr "**如何迁移：** 没有直接替代品。请移除任何指向 `/ui` 端点的链接或集成。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:67
msgid "`:rev` filter syntax changed; `:from` and `:concat` removed"
msgstr "`:rev` 过滤器语法已变更；`:from` 和 `:concat` 已移除"

#: src/guide/migration.md:71
msgid ""
"The `:rev` filter now requires an explicit match operator before each SHA, "
"and the zero-SHA shorthand for the default case has been replaced by `_`."
msgstr ""
"`:rev` 过滤器现在要求在每个 SHA 前使用显式匹配操作符，并且默认情况的 zero-SHA "
"简写已替换为 `_`。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:74
msgid "**What changed:**"
msgstr "**变更内容：**"

#: src/guide/migration.md:76
msgid "The old syntax used a bare SHA for each entry:"
msgstr "旧语法为每个条目使用裸 SHA："

#: src/guide/migration.md:80
msgid ""
"The new syntax requires an operator prefix and uses `_` for the default case:"
msgstr "新语法要求使用操作符前缀，并用 `_` 表示默认情况："

#: src/guide/migration.md:85
msgid "Available operators:"
msgstr "可用操作符："

#: src/guide/migration.md:87
msgid ""
"`<=sha` — matches the commit and all its ancestors (inclusive); equivalent "
"to the old bare-SHA behavior"
msgstr "`<=sha` — 匹配该提交及其所有祖先（含自身）；等同于旧的裸 SHA 行为"

#: src/guide/migration.md:89
msgid ""
"`<sha` — matches only strict ancestors (excludes the named commit itself)"
msgstr "`<sha` — 仅匹配严格祖先（不包括命名提交本身）"

#: src/guide/migration.md:90
msgid "`==sha` — matches only the exact commit"
msgstr "`==sha` — 仅匹配确切的提交"

#: src/guide/migration.md:92
msgid "**How to migrate `:rev` filters:**"
msgstr "**如何迁移 `:rev` 过滤器：**"

#: src/guide/migration.md:94
msgid "Replace each bare `sha:filter` entry with `<=sha:filter`"
msgstr "将每个裸 `sha:filter` 条目替换为 `<=sha:filter`"

#: src/guide/migration.md:95
msgid ""
"Replace `0000000000000000000000000000000000000000:filter` with `_:filter`"
msgstr "将 `0000000000000000000000000000000000000000:filter` 替换为 `_:filter`"

#: src/guide/migration.md:97
msgid "**`:from` removed:**"
msgstr "**`:from` 已移除：**"

#: src/guide/migration.md:99
msgid ""
"The `:from(sha:filter)` filter has been removed. It kept the original "
"history up to and including `sha` unchanged and applied `filter` to all "
"later commits."
msgstr ""
"`:from(sha:filter)` 过滤器已被移除。它会保持截至并包含 `sha` 的原始历史不变，"
"并将 `filter` 应用于之后的所有提交。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:102
msgid "Equivalent `:rev` expression:"
msgstr "等价的 `:rev` 表达式："

#: src/guide/migration.md:107
msgid "**`:concat` removed:**"
msgstr "**`:concat` 已移除：**"

#: src/guide/migration.md:109
msgid ""
"The `:concat(sha:filter)` filter has been removed. It was the internal "
"building block of `:from` and sometimes appeared in normalized filter output "
"(e.g. from `josh-filter -p`). Filters of the form `filter:concat(sha:"
"filter)` are equivalent to `:from(sha:filter)` and should be migrated to:"
msgstr ""
"`:concat(sha:filter)` 过滤器已被移除。它曾是 `:from` 的内部构建块，有时会出现"
"在规范化后的过滤器输出中（例如来自 `josh-filter -p`）。形如 `filter:concat(sha:"
"filter)` 的过滤器等价于 `:from(sha:filter)`，应迁移为："

#: src/guide/migration.md:117
msgid "Cache location changed"
msgstr "缓存位置已变更"

#: src/guide/migration.md:121
msgid ""
"The local sled cache is now stored at `.git/josh/cache` instead of `.git/"
"josh`."
msgstr "本地 sled 缓存现在存储在 `.git/josh/cache`，而不是 `.git/josh`。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:123
msgid ""
"**What changed:** On the first run after upgrading, Josh will not find any "
"existing cache entries and will recompute all filter results from scratch. "
"This is a one-time cost."
msgstr ""
"**变更内容：** 升级后的首次运行中，Josh 将找不到任何现有缓存条目，并会从头"
"重新计算所有过滤结果。这是一次性成本。"

#: src/guide/migration.md:126
msgid ""
"**No action required** for most users - the cache will be rebuilt "
"automatically. If you have scripts or tooling that reference `.git/josh` "
"directly (e.g. to delete or back up the cache), update them to point to `."
"git/josh/cache` instead."
msgstr ""
"对大多数用户而言**无需操作**——缓存会自动重建。如果你有脚本或工具直接引用 "
"`.git/josh`（例如用于删除或备份缓存），请将它们更新为指向 `.git/josh/cache`。"

