#: src/reference/cli.md:276
msgid ""
"Run a workspace in an isolated, automatically-cached container. See [josh "
"compose run](../contributing/josh-run.md) for full documentation."
msgstr ""
"在隔离且自动缓存的容器中运行 workspace。完整文档请参见 [josh compose run]"
"(../contributing/josh-run.md)。"

#: src/reference/cli.md:285 src/contributing/josh-run.md:71
msgid "`[REFERENCE]`"
msgstr "`[REFERENCE]`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:285
msgid ""
"Git ref to build from: `.` (working tree), `+` (index), `HEAD`, or any ref "
"(default: `.`)"
msgstr "用于构建的 git ref：`.`（工作树）、`+`（索引）、`HEAD` 或任意 ref（默认：`.`）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:286 src/contributing/josh-run.md:72
msgid "`[FILTER]`"
msgstr "`[FILTER]`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:286
msgid ""
"Filter selecting the workspace to run (default: `:+compose`, reads `compose."
"josh` in the repo root)"
msgstr "选择要运行的 workspace 的过滤器（默认：`:+compose`，读取仓库根目录中的 `compose.josh`）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:292 src/contributing/josh-run.md:87
msgid "`--clean`"
msgstr "`--clean`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:292 src/contributing/josh-run.md:87
msgid "Remove cached images and output volumes"
msgstr "移除缓存镜像和输出卷"

#: src/reference/cli.md:293 src/contributing/josh-run.md:88
msgid "`--clean-all`"
msgstr "`--clean-all`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:293 src/contributing/josh-run.md:88
msgid "Remove cached images, output volumes, and persistent cache volumes"
msgstr "移除缓存镜像、输出卷和持久缓存卷"

#: src/reference/cli.md:310
msgid "josh-filter (standalone binary)"
msgstr "josh-filter（独立二进制文件）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:312
msgid ""
"`josh-filter` is a lower-level command that rewrites git history using Josh "
"filter specs. It is intended for scripting and one-off history rewriting "
"tasks rather than day-to-day development workflows."
msgstr ""
"`josh-filter` 是一个较低层级的命令，会使用 Josh 过滤器规格重写 git 历史。它"
"面向脚本和一次性历史重写任务，而不是日常开发工作流。"

#: src/reference/cli.md:316
msgid ""
"**Input:** the second positional argument selects what to filter. It "
"defaults to `HEAD` but can be any of:"
msgstr "**输入：** 第二个位置参数选择要过滤的对象。它默认是 `HEAD`，但也可以是："

#: src/reference/cli.md:319
msgid "`.` - the working tree (including uncommitted changes)"
msgstr "`.` - 工作树（包括未提交变更）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:320
msgid "`+` - the index (staged changes only)"
msgstr "`+` - 索引（仅暂存变更）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:321
msgid "A full or abbreviated commit SHA"
msgstr "完整或缩写的提交 SHA"

#: src/reference/cli.md:322
msgid "A ref name (e.g. `main`, `refs/heads/feature`)"
msgstr "ref 名称（例如 `main`、`refs/heads/feature`）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:324
msgid ""
"**Output:** the filtered commit SHA is printed to stdout. The filtered "
"history is also written to the ref given by `--update` (default: "
"`FILTERED_HEAD`)."
msgstr ""
"**输出：** 过滤后的提交 SHA 会打印到 stdout。过滤后的历史也会写入 `--update` "
"给定的 ref（默认：`FILTERED_HEAD`）。"

#: src/reference/cli.md:327
msgid "**Basic usage:**"
msgstr "**基本用法：**"

#: src/reference/cli.md:344
msgid "`--update <ref>`"
msgstr "`--update <ref>`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:344
msgid "Ref to update with the filtered result (default: `FILTERED_HEAD`)"
msgstr "用过滤结果更新的 ref（默认：`FILTERED_HEAD`）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:345
msgid "`--file <path>`"
msgstr "`--file <path>`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:345
msgid "Read filter spec from a file"
msgstr "从文件读取过滤器规格"

#: src/reference/cli.md:346
msgid "`--squash-pattern <pattern>`"
msgstr "`--squash-pattern <pattern>`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:346
msgid "Squash commits matching the pattern"
msgstr "压缩匹配该模式的提交"

#: src/reference/cli.md:347
msgid "`--squash-file <path>`"
msgstr "`--squash-file <path>`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:347
msgid "Read squash patterns from a file"
msgstr "从文件读取 squash 模式"

#: src/reference/cli.md:348
msgid "`--single`"
msgstr "`--single`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:348
msgid "Produce a single squashed commit"
msgstr "生成单个压缩后的提交"

#: src/reference/cli.md:349
msgid "`-d`"
msgstr "`-d`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:349
msgid "Discovery mode: populate cache with probable filters"
msgstr "发现模式：使用可能的过滤器填充缓存"

#: src/reference/cli.md:350
msgid "`-t`"
msgstr "`-t`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:350
msgid "Output Chrome tracing data"
msgstr "输出 Chrome tracing 数据"

#: src/reference/cli.md:351
msgid "`-p`"
msgstr "`-p`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:351
msgid "Print the filter spec (and exit)"
msgstr "打印过滤器规格（然后退出）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:352
msgid "`-i`"
msgstr "`-i`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:352
msgid "Print the filter ID (and exit)"
msgstr "打印过滤器 ID（然后退出）"

#: src/reference/cli.md:353
msgid "`-s`"
msgstr "`-s`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:353
msgid "Print cache statistics"
msgstr "打印缓存统计信息"

#: src/reference/cli.md:354
msgid "`-n`"
msgstr "`-n`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:354
msgid "Skip loading the cache"
msgstr "跳过加载缓存"

#: src/reference/cli.md:355
msgid "`--distributed-cache`"
msgstr "`--distributed-cache`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:355
msgid "Enable the distributed cache backend"
msgstr "启用分布式缓存后端"

#: src/reference/cli.md:356
msgid "`--reverse`"
msgstr "`--reverse`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:356
msgid ""
"Reverse-apply the filter (unapply): reconstruct upstream commits from "
"filtered ones"
msgstr "反向应用过滤器（取消应用）：根据过滤后的提交重建上游提交"

#: src/reference/cli.md:357
msgid "`--check-roundtrip`"
msgstr "`--check-roundtrip`"

#: src/reference/cli.md:357
msgid ""
"When used with `--reverse`, verify that applying the filter to the reverse "
"result reproduces the original commit. Exits with code 1 if the check fails."
msgstr ""
"与 `--reverse` 一起使用时，验证对反向结果应用过滤器是否能复现原始提交。如果"
"检查失败，则以代码 1 退出。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:2
msgid "History filtering"
msgstr "历史过滤"

#: src/reference/filters.md:4
msgid ""
"Josh transforms commits by applying filters to them. As any commit in git "
"represents not just a single state of the file system but also its entire "
"history, applying a filter to a commit produces an entirely new history. The "
"result of a filter is a normal git commit and therefore can be filtered "
"again, making filters chainable."
msgstr ""
"Josh 通过对提交应用过滤器来转换提交。由于 git 中的任何提交不仅表示文件系统的"
"单一状态，也表示其完整历史，因此对提交应用过滤器会生成一段全新的历史。过滤器"
"的结果是一个普通 git 提交，因此可以再次过滤，这让过滤器可以链式组合。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:10 src/contributing/josh-run.md:63
msgid "Syntax"
msgstr "语法"

#: src/reference/filters.md:12
msgid "Filters always begin with a colon and can be chained:"
msgstr "过滤器始终以冒号开头，并且可以链式组合："

#: src/reference/filters.md:16
msgid ""
"When used as part of an URL filters cannot contain white space or newlines. "
"When read from a file however white space can be inserted between filters "
"(not after the leading colon). Additionally newlines can be used instead of "
"`,` inside of composition filters."
msgstr ""
"作为 URL 的一部分使用时，过滤器不能包含空白或换行。不过，从文件读取时，可以"
"在过滤器之间插入空白（但不能放在开头冒号之后）。此外，在组合过滤器内部可以"
"使用换行代替 `,`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:20
msgid ""
"Some filters take arguments, and arguments can optionally be quoted using "
"double quotes, if special characters used by the filter language need to be "
"used (like `:` or space):"
msgstr ""
"某些过滤器接受参数；如果需要使用过滤器语言中的特殊字符（例如 `:` 或空格），"
"参数可以选择用双引号引用："

#: src/reference/filters.md:23
msgid ""
"    :filter=argument1,\"argument2\"\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    :filter=argument1,\"argument2\"\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/filters.md:25
msgid "Filter options **`:~(key1=\"value1\",key2=\"value2\")[:filter]`**"
msgstr "过滤器选项 **`:~(key1=\"value1\",key2=\"value2\")[:filter]`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:27
msgid ""
"The `:~(...)[]` syntax allows you to provide filter options (metadata) that "
"affect how the filter is applied. The options are specified as key-value "
"pairs in parentheses, followed by the actual filter in square brackets."
msgstr ""
"`:~(...)[]` 语法允许你提供影响过滤器应用方式的过滤器选项（元数据）。选项以"
"括号中的键值对指定，后面跟着方括号中的实际过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:31 src/reference/filters.md:253
msgid "**Syntax:**"
msgstr "**语法：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:32
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(option1=\"value1\",option2=\"value2\")[:filter]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(option1=\"value1\",option2=\"value2\")[:filter]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:36
msgid ""
"Multiple options can be specified by separating them with commas. Option "
"values must be quoted using double quotes."
msgstr "可以用逗号分隔来指定多个选项。选项值必须使用双引号引用。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:40
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(key1=\"value1\",key2=\"value2\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(key1=\"value1\",key2=\"value2\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:44
msgid ""
"This applies the `:/sub1` filter with the specified options attached as "
"metadata."
msgstr "这会应用 `:/sub1` 过滤器，并将指定选项作为元数据附加到该过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:46
msgid "History option"
msgstr "History 选项"

#: src/reference/filters.md:48
msgid ""
"The `history` option controls how the commit history is processed during "
"filtering. It affects both how commits are walked and how merge commits are "
"handled in the output history."
msgstr ""
"`history` 选项控制过滤过程中提交历史的处理方式。它会同时影响提交遍历方式和"
"输出历史中 merge commit 的处理方式。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:51 src/reference/filters.md:85
msgid "**Available values:**"
msgstr "**可用值：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:53
msgid ""
"**`history=\"linear\"`** - Produces a linear history by converting merge "
"commits into regular commits, creating a linear chain of commits in the "
"output history."
msgstr ""
"**`history=\"linear\"`** - 通过将 merge commit 转换为普通提交来生成线性历史，"
"在输出历史中创建一条线性提交链。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:57
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(history=\"linear\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(history=\"linear\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:61
msgid ""
"**`history=\"keep-trivial-merges\"`** - Prevents dropping trivial merge "
"commits that would normally be pruned from the output history."
msgstr ""
"**`history=\"keep-trivial-merges\"`** - 防止丢弃通常会从输出历史中剪除的平凡"
" merge commit。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:64
msgid ""
"Normally, Josh will drop merge commits from the filtered history if their "
"filtered tree is identical to the first parent's tree. Setting this option "
"to `\"keep-trivial-merges\"` preserves these commits in the output history."
msgstr ""
"通常，如果某个 merge commit 的过滤后 tree 与其第一个父提交的 tree 相同，Josh "
"会从过滤后的历史中丢弃该 merge commit。将此选项设置为 `\"keep-trivial-merges\"` "
"会在输出历史中保留这些提交。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:69
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(history=\"keep-trivial-merges\")[::file1]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(history=\"keep-trivial-merges\")[::file1]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:73
msgid ""
"**Note for users of older versions:** In older versions of Josh, `\"keep-"
"trivial-merges\"` was the default behavior. If you're upgrading from an "
"older version and need to recreate the same history structure, you should "
"explicitly set `history=\"keep-trivial-merges\"` in your filter options."
msgstr ""
"**旧版本用户注意：** 在较旧版本的 Josh 中，`\"keep-trivial-merges\"` 是默认"
"行为。如果你正从旧版本升级，并且需要重建相同的历史结构，应在过滤器选项中显式"
"设置 `history=\"keep-trivial-merges\"`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:77
msgid "Gpgsig option"
msgstr "Gpgsig 选项"

#: src/reference/filters.md:79
msgid ""
"The `gpgsig` option controls how PGP/GPG signature headers (`gpgsig`) in "
"commit objects are handled during filtering."
msgstr "`gpgsig` 选项控制过滤过程中如何处理提交对象中的 PGP/GPG 签名头（`gpgsig`）。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:82
msgid ""
"By default Josh preserves the `gpgsig` header byte-for-byte. This keeps the "
"commit hash stable across round-trips but makes the signature invalid (since "
"the tree and parent references change)."
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，Josh 会逐字节保留 `gpgsig` 头。这会让提交哈希在往返转换中保持"
"稳定，但会使签名失效（因为 tree 和父引用发生了变化）。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:87
msgid ""
"**`gpgsig=\"remove\"`** - Strips the `gpgsig` header from every filtered "
"commit. Equivalent to the `:unsign` shorthand filter."
msgstr ""
"**`gpgsig=\"remove\"`** - 从每个过滤后的提交中剥离 `gpgsig` 头。等同于 "
"`:unsign` 简写过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:91
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(gpgsig=\"remove\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(gpgsig=\"remove\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:95
msgid ""
"**`gpgsig=\"norm-lf\"`** - Normalizes `\\r\\n` line endings to `\\n` inside "
"the `gpgsig` header before writing the filtered commit."
msgstr ""
"**`gpgsig=\"norm-lf\"`** - 在写入过滤后的提交前，将 `gpgsig` 头内部的 `\\r\\n` "
"换行符规范化为 `\\n`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:98
msgid ""
"The standard git commit object format uses `\\n` line endings throughout, "
"including inside `gpgsig` headers. Some signing tools or forges write "
"`\\r\\n` instead, which is technically non-standard but valid as far as git "
"is concerned — git treats the header value as opaque bytes. Josh preserves "
"whichever line endings are present in the original commit."
msgstr ""
"标准 git 提交对象格式全程使用 `\\n` 换行符，包括 `gpgsig` 头内部。一些签名工具"
"或代码托管平台会改写为 `\\r\\n`，这在技术上不符合标准，但对 git 来说仍是有效"
"的——git 会将头值视为不透明字节。Josh 会保留原始提交中存在的任何换行符。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:103
msgid ""
"An older version of Josh accidentally normalized `\\r\\n` to `\\n` during "
"filtering. This option restores that behavior and is intended **only** for "
"deployments that need to reproduce a history produced by the old version — "
"both variants represent the same logical content but produce different "
"commit hashes, causing history to diverge."
msgstr ""
"较旧版本的 Josh 在过滤过程中曾意外地将 `\\r\\n` 规范化为 `\\n`。此选项会恢复"
"该行为，并且**仅**面向需要复现旧版本生成历史的部署——两种形式表示相同的逻辑内容，"
"但会生成不同提交哈希，导致历史分叉。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:109
msgid ""
"```\n"
":~(gpgsig=\"norm-lf\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":~(gpgsig=\"norm-lf\")[:/sub1]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:113
msgid "Available filters"
msgstr "可用过滤器"

#: src/reference/filters.md:115
msgid "Subdirectory **`:/a`**"
msgstr "子目录 **`:/a`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:116
msgid ""
"Take only the selected subdirectory from the input and make it the root of "
"the filtered tree. Note that `:/a/b` and `:/a:/b` are equivalent ways to get "
"the same result."
msgstr ""
"仅从输入中取出选中的子目录，并使其成为过滤后 tree 的根。注意，`:/a/b` 和 "
"`:/a:/b` 是得到相同结果的等价写法。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:120
msgid "Directory **`::a/`**"
msgstr "目录 **`::a/`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:121
msgid ""
"A shorthand for the commonly occurring filter combination `:/a:prefix=a`."
msgstr "常见过滤器组合 `:/a:prefix=a` 的简写。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:123
msgid "File **`::a`** or **`::destination=source`**"
msgstr "文件 **`::a`** 或 **`::destination=source`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:124
msgid "Produces a tree with only the specified file."
msgstr "生成一个仅包含指定文件的 tree。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:126
msgid ""
"When using a single argument (`::a`), the file is placed at the same full "
"path as in the source tree. When using the `destination=source` syntax (`::"
"destination=source`), the file is renamed from `source` to `destination` in "
"the filtered tree."
msgstr ""
"使用单个参数（`::a`）时，文件会放在与源 tree 中相同的完整路径下。使用 "
"`destination=source` 语法（`::destination=source`）时，该文件会在过滤后的 tree "
"中从 `source` 重命名为 `destination`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:129
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr "示例："

#: src/reference/filters.md:130
msgid "`::file.txt` - Selects `file.txt` and places it at `file.txt`"
msgstr "`::file.txt` - 选择 `file.txt` 并将其放在 `file.txt`"

#: src/reference/filters.md:131
msgid ""
"`::src/file.txt` - Selects `src/file.txt` and places it at `src/file.txt`"
msgstr "`::src/file.txt` - 选择 `src/file.txt` 并将其放在 `src/file.txt`"

#: src/reference/filters.md:132
msgid ""
"`::renamed.txt=src/original.txt` - Selects `src/original.txt` and places it "
"at `renamed.txt`"
msgstr "`::renamed.txt=src/original.txt` - 选择 `src/original.txt` 并将其放在 `renamed.txt`"

#: src/reference/filters.md:133
msgid ""
"`::subdir/file.txt=src/file.txt` - Selects `src/file.txt` and places it at "
"`subdir/file.txt`"
msgstr "`::subdir/file.txt=src/file.txt` - 选择 `src/file.txt` 并将其放在 `subdir/file.txt`"

#: src/reference/filters.md:135
msgid ""
"Note that `::a/b` is equivalent to `::a/::b`. Pattern filters (with `*`) "
"cannot be combined with the `destination=source` syntax."
msgstr ""
"注意，`::a/b` 等同于 `::a/::b`。模式过滤器（带 `*`）不能与 "
"`destination=source` 语法组合使用。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:138
msgid "Prefix **`:prefix=a`**"
msgstr "前缀 **`:prefix=a`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:139
msgid ""
"Take the input tree and place it into subdirectory `a`. Note that `:prefix=a/"
"b` and `:prefix=b:prefix=a` are equivalent."
msgstr "取输入 tree 并将其放入子目录 `a`。注意，`:prefix=a/b` 和 `:prefix=b:prefix=a` 等价。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:142
msgid "Composition **`:[:filter1,:filter2,...,:filterN]`**"
msgstr "组合 **`:[:filter1,:filter2,...,:filterN]`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:143
msgid ""
"Compose a tree by overlaying the outputs of `:filter1` ... `:filterN` on top "
"of each other. It is guaranteed that each file will only appear at most once "
"in the output. The first filter that consumes a file is the one deciding "
"it's mapped location. Therefore the order in which filters are composed "
"matters."
msgstr ""
"通过将 `:filter1` ... `:filterN` 的输出相互叠加来组合一个 tree。保证每个文件"
"在输出中最多只出现一次。第一个消费某个文件的过滤器会决定它的映射位置。因此，"
"过滤器的组合顺序很重要。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:148
msgid ""
"Inside of a composition `x=:filter` can be used as an alternative spelling "
"for `:filter:prefix=x`."
msgstr "在组合内部，`x=:filter` 可作为 `:filter:prefix=x` 的另一种写法。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:151
msgid "Exclusion **`:exclude[:filter]`**"
msgstr "排除 **`:exclude[:filter]`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:152
msgid ""
"Remove all paths present in the _output_ of `:filter` from the input tree. "
"It should generally be avoided to use any filters that change paths and "
"instead only use filters that select paths without altering them."
msgstr ""
"从输入 tree 中移除 `:filter` _输出_中存在的所有路径。通常应避免使用任何会改变"
"路径的过滤器，而只使用选择路径但不修改路径的过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:156
msgid "Invert **`:invert[:filter]`**"
msgstr "反转 **`:invert[:filter]`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:157
msgid ""
"A shorthand syntax that applies the inverse of the composed filter. The "
"inverse of a filter is a filter that undoes the transformation. For example, "
"the inverse of `:/sub1` (subdirectory) is `:prefix=sub1` (prefix), and vice "
"versa."
msgstr ""
"用于应用组合过滤器反向形式的简写语法。过滤器的反向形式是撤销该转换的过滤器。"
"例如，`:/sub1`（子目录）的反向是 `:prefix=sub1`（前缀），反之亦然。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:165
msgid ""
"This is equivalent to `:prefix=sub1`, which takes the input tree and places "
"it into the `sub1` subdirectory."
msgstr "这等同于 `:prefix=sub1`，它会取输入 tree 并将其放入 `sub1` 子目录。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:168
msgid "Multiple filters can be provided in the compose:"
msgstr "可以在 compose 中提供多个过滤器："

#: src/reference/filters.md:172
msgid "This inverts the composition of `:/sub1` and `:/sub2`."
msgstr "这会反转 `:/sub1` 和 `:/sub2` 的组合。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:174
msgid "Scope **`:<X>[..]`**"
msgstr "作用域 **`:<X>[..]`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:175
msgid "A shorthand syntax that expands to `:X:[..]:invert[:X]`, where:"
msgstr "会展开为 `:X:[..]:invert[:X]` 的简写语法，其中："

#: src/reference/filters.md:176
msgid "`:X` is a filter (without built-in compose)"
msgstr "`:X` 是一个过滤器（不含内置 compose）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:177
msgid "`:[..]` is a compose filter (like in `:exclude`)"
msgstr "`:[..]` 是一个 compose 过滤器（类似 `:exclude` 中的用法）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:179
msgid ""
"This filter first applies `:X` to scope the input, then applies the compose "
"filter `:[..]`, and finally inverts `:X` to restore the original scope. This "
"is useful when you want to apply a composition filter within a specific "
"scope and then restore the original structure."
msgstr ""
"此过滤器首先应用 `:X` 来限定输入作用域，然后应用 compose 过滤器 `:[..]`，最后"
"反转 `:X` 以恢复原始作用域。当你想在特定作用域内应用组合过滤器，然后恢复原始"
"结构时，这会很有用。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:187
msgid "This is equivalent to `:/sub1:[::file1,::file2]:invert[:/sub1]`, which:"
msgstr "这等同于 `:/sub1:[::file1,::file2]:invert[:/sub1]`，它会："

#: src/reference/filters.md:188
msgid "Selects the `sub1` subdirectory (applies `:/sub1`)"
msgstr "选择 `sub1` 子目录（应用 `:/sub1`）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:189
msgid ""
"Applies the composition filter to select `file1` and `file2` (applies `:[::"
"file1,::file2]`)"
msgstr "应用组合过滤器来选择 `file1` 和 `file2`（应用 `:[::file1,::file2]`）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:190
msgid ""
"Restores the original scope by inverting the subdirectory selection (applies "
"`:invert[:/sub1]`)"
msgstr "通过反转子目录选择来恢复原始作用域（应用 `:invert[:/sub1]`）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:192
msgid "Stored **`:+path/to/file`**"
msgstr "存储式 **`:+path/to/file`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:193
msgid ""
"Looks for a file with a `.josh` extension at the specified path and applies "
"the filter defined in that file. The path argument should be provided "
"_without_ the `.josh` extension, as it will be automatically appended."
msgstr ""
"在指定路径查找带 `.josh` 扩展名的文件，并应用该文件中定义的过滤器。路径参数"
"应_不带_ `.josh` 扩展名，因为它会被自动附加。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:196
msgid ""
"For example, `:+st/config` will look for a file at `st/config.josh` and "
"apply the filter defined in that file. The resulting tree will contain the "
"contents specified by the filter in the `.josh` file."
msgstr ""
"例如，`:+st/config` 会查找 `st/config.josh` 文件，并应用该文件中定义的过滤器。"
"生成的 tree 将包含 `.josh` 文件中过滤器指定的内容。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:199
msgid ""
"Stored filters apply from the root of the repository, making them useful for "
"configuration files that define filters to be applied at the repository root "
"level."
msgstr ""
"存储式过滤器会从仓库根目录应用，因此适合用于定义应在仓库根级别应用的过滤器的"
"配置文件。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:202
msgid "Workspace **`:workspace=a`**"
msgstr "Workspace **`:workspace=a`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:203
msgid ""
"Like stored filters, but with an additional \"base\" component that first "
"selects the specified directory (called the \"workspace root\") before "
"applying the filter from the `workspace.josh` file inside it."
msgstr ""
"类似存储式过滤器，但带有一个额外的 \"base\" 组件，会先选择指定目录（称为 "
"\"workspace root\"），然后应用其中 `workspace.josh` 文件里的过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:206
msgid ""
"The workspace filter is equivalent to `:/a` combined with applying a stored "
"filter, where the filter is read from `workspace.josh` within the selected "
"directory. The resulting tree will contain the contents of the workspace "
"root as well as additional files specified in the `workspace.josh` file. "
"(see [Workspaces](./workspace.md))"
msgstr ""
"workspace 过滤器等同于 `:/a` 与存储式过滤器的组合，其中过滤器会从所选目录内的 "
"`workspace.josh` 读取。生成的 tree 将包含 workspace root 的内容，以及 "
"`workspace.josh` 文件中指定的额外文件。（参见 [Workspaces](./workspace.md)）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:211
msgid ""
"Text replacement **`:replace(\"regex_0\":\"replacement_0\",...,\"regex_N\":"
"\"replacement_N\")`**"
msgstr ""
"文本替换 **`:replace(\"regex_0\":\"replacement_0\",...,\"regex_N\":"
"\"replacement_N\")`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:212
msgid ""
"Applies the supplied regular expressions to every file in the input tree."
msgstr "将提供的正则表达式应用到输入 tree 中的每个文件。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:214
msgid "Signature removal **`:unsign`**"
msgstr "移除签名 **`:unsign`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:215
msgid ""
"The default behaviour of Josh is to copy, if it exists, the signature of the "
"original commit in the filtered commit. This makes the signature invalid, "
"but allows a perfect round-trip: josh will be able to recreate the original "
"commit from the filtered one."
msgstr ""
"Josh 的默认行为是，如果原始提交存在签名，就将其复制到过滤后的提交中。这会使"
"签名失效，但允许完美往返：josh 能够根据过滤后的提交重建原始提交。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:219
msgid ""
"This behaviour might not be desirable, and this filter drops the signatures "
"from the history. It is a shorthand for `:~(gpgsig=\"remove\")[:/]`. See the "
"[gpgsig option](#gpgsig-option) for additional gpgsig-related options."
msgstr ""
"这种行为可能并不总是理想的，而此过滤器会从历史中丢弃签名。它是 "
"`:~(gpgsig=\"remove\")[:/]` 的简写。更多 gpgsig 相关选项请参见 [gpgsig 选项]"
"(#gpgsig-option)。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:223
msgid "Pattern filters"
msgstr "模式过滤器"

#: src/reference/filters.md:225
msgid ""
"The following filters accept a glob like pattern `X` that can contain `*` to "
"match any number of characters. Note that two or more consecutive wildcards "
"(`**`) are not allowed."
msgstr ""
"以下过滤器接受类似 glob 的模式 `X`，其中可包含 `*` 来匹配任意数量的字符。注意，"
"不允许使用两个或更多连续通配符（`**`）。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:229
msgid "Match directories **`::X/`**"
msgstr "匹配目录 **`::X/`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:230
msgid "All matching subdirectories in the input root"
msgstr "输入根目录中所有匹配的子目录"

#: src/reference/filters.md:232
msgid "Match files or directories **`::X`**"
msgstr "匹配文件或目录 **`::X`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:233
msgid "All matching files or directories in the input root"
msgstr "输入根目录中所有匹配的文件或目录"

#: src/reference/filters.md:235
msgid "Match nested directories **`::**/X/`**"
msgstr "匹配嵌套目录 **`::**/X/`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:236
msgid ""
"All subdirectories matching the pattern in arbitrarily deep subdirectories "
"of the input"
msgstr "输入中任意深度子目录内所有匹配该模式的子目录"

#: src/reference/filters.md:238
msgid "Match nested files **`::**/X`**"
msgstr "匹配嵌套文件 **`::**/X`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:239
msgid ""
"All files matching the pattern in arbitrarily deep subdirectories of the "
"input"
msgstr "输入中任意深度子目录内所有匹配该模式的文件"

#: src/reference/filters.md:241
msgid "History filters"
msgstr "历史过滤器"

#: src/reference/filters.md:243
msgid ""
"These filter do not modify git trees, but instead only operate on the commit "
"graph."
msgstr "这些过滤器不会修改 git tree，而只作用于提交图。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:245
msgid "Linearise history **:linear\\[:filter\\]**"
msgstr "线性化历史 **:linear\\[:filter\\]**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:246
msgid ""
"Produce a filtered history that does not contain any merge commits. This is "
"done by simply dropping all parents except the first on every commit."
msgstr "生成不包含任何 merge commit 的过滤历史。实现方式是在每个提交上简单丢弃除第一个父提交外的所有父提交。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:249
msgid "Filter specific parts of the history **:rev(...)**"
msgstr "过滤历史的特定部分 **:rev(...)**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:251
msgid ""
"The `:rev(...)` filter allows you to apply different filters to different "
"parts of the commit history based on commit relationships. Each entry in the "
"filter specifies a condition and a filter to apply when that condition "
"matches."
msgstr ""
"`:rev(...)` 过滤器允许你基于提交关系，对提交历史的不同部分应用不同过滤器。"
"过滤器中的每个条目都会指定一个条件，以及条件匹配时要应用的过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:262
msgid ""
"Commit references must be **full 40-character SHA-1 hashes**; short/"
"abbreviated SHAs are not accepted."
msgstr "提交引用必须是**完整的 40 字符 SHA-1 哈希**；不接受短 SHA 或缩写 SHA。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:264
msgid "**Operators:**"
msgstr "**操作符：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:266
msgid ""
"**`<`** - Strict ancestor match: matches if the commit is an ancestor of "
"`<sha>` AND the commit is not equal to `<sha>`"
msgstr "**`<`** - 严格祖先匹配：如果该提交是 `<sha>` 的祖先，且该提交不等于 `<sha>`，则匹配"

#: src/reference/filters.md:267
msgid ""
"**`<=`** - Inclusive ancestor match: matches if the commit is an ancestor of "
"`<sha>` OR the commit equals `<sha>`"
msgstr "**`<=`** - 包含式祖先匹配：如果该提交是 `<sha>` 的祖先，或该提交等于 `<sha>`，则匹配"

#: src/reference/filters.md:268
msgid "**`==`** - Exact match: matches only if the commit equals `<sha>`"
msgstr "**`==`** - 精确匹配：仅当该提交等于 `<sha>` 时匹配"

#: src/reference/filters.md:269
msgid ""
"**`_`** - Default filter: matches any commit that doesn't match any previous "
"condition (no SHA needed)"
msgstr "**`_`** - 默认过滤器：匹配任何未匹配前面条件的提交（不需要 SHA）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:271
msgid "**Matching behavior:**"
msgstr "**匹配行为：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:273
msgid "Rules are evaluated in the order they are specified"
msgstr "规则会按指定顺序求值"

#: src/reference/filters.md:274
msgid ""
"**First match wins** - once a condition matches, that filter is applied and "
"no further rules are checked"
msgstr "**首次匹配优先** - 一旦条件匹配，就会应用该过滤器，并且不再检查后续规则"

#: src/reference/filters.md:275
msgid ""
"The default filter (`_`) will match any commit that hasn't matched a "
"previous rule, making any rules after it unreachable"
msgstr "默认过滤器（`_`）会匹配任何未匹配前面规则的提交，因此它后面的任何规则都不可达"

#: src/reference/filters.md:282
msgid ""
"This applies `:prefix=old` to commit `abc12345...` and all its ancestors, "
"and `:prefix=new` only to commit `def45678...`."
msgstr "这会将 `:prefix=old` 应用于提交 `abc12345...` 及其所有祖先，并仅将 `:prefix=new` 应用于提交 `def45678...`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:287
msgid ""
"This applies `:prefix=old` to all ancestors of that commit (but not the "
"commit itself), and `:prefix=default` to all other commits (including that "
"commit and any commits after it)."
msgstr ""
"这会将 `:prefix=old` 应用于该提交的所有祖先（但不包括该提交本身），并将 "
"`:prefix=default` 应用于所有其他提交（包括该提交及其之后的任何提交）。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:289
msgid "Prune trivial merge commits **:prune=trivial-merge**"
msgstr "剪除平凡 merge commit **:prune=trivial-merge**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:291
msgid ""
"Produce a history that skips all merge commits whose tree is identical to "
"the first parents tree. Normally Josh will keep all commits in the filtered "
"history whose tree differs from any of it's parents."
msgstr ""
"生成一段历史，跳过所有 tree 与第一个父提交 tree 相同的 merge commit。通常，"
"Josh 会在过滤后的历史中保留 tree 与任一父提交不同的所有提交。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:296
msgid ""
"Commit message rewriting **`:\"template\"`** or **`:\"template\";\"regex\"`**"
msgstr "提交消息重写 **`:\"template\"`** 或 **`:\"template\";\"regex\"`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:298
msgid ""
"Rewrite commit messages using a template string. The template can use regex "
"capture groups to extract and reformat parts of the original commit message, "
"as well as special template variables for commit metadata."
msgstr ""
"使用模板字符串重写提交消息。模板可以使用正则捕获组来提取并重新格式化原始提交"
"消息的部分内容，也可以使用表示提交元数据的特殊模板变量。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:302
msgid "**Simple message replacement:**"
msgstr "**简单消息替换：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:303
msgid ""
"```\n"
":\"New message\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":\"New message\"\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:306
msgid "This replaces all commit messages with \"New message\"."
msgstr "这会将所有提交消息替换为 \"New message\"。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:308
msgid "**Using regex with named capture groups:**"
msgstr "**使用带命名捕获组的正则：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:309
msgid ""
"```\n"
":\"[{type}] {message}\";\"(?s)^(?P<type>fix|feat|docs): (?P<message>.+)$\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":\"[{type}] {message}\";\"(?s)^(?P<type>fix|feat|docs): (?P<message>.+)$\"\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:312
msgid ""
"This uses a regex to match the original commit message and extract named "
"capture groups (`{type}` and `{message}`) which are then used in the "
"template. The regex `(?s)^(?P<type>fix|feat|docs): (?P<message>.+)$` matches "
"commit messages starting with \"fix:\", \"feat:\", or \"docs:\" followed by "
"a message, and the template reformats them as `[type] message`."
msgstr ""
"这会使用正则匹配原始提交消息，并提取命名捕获组（`{type}` 和 `{message}`），"
"随后在模板中使用它们。正则 `(?s)^(?P<type>fix|feat|docs): (?P<message>.+)$` "
"会匹配以 \"fix:\"、\"feat:\" 或 \"docs:\" 开头并跟随消息的提交消息，模板会将"
"其重新格式化为 `[type] message`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:317
msgid ""
"**Using template variables:** The template supports special variables that "
"provide access to commit metadata:"
msgstr "**使用模板变量：** 模板支持用于访问提交元数据的特殊变量："

#: src/reference/filters.md:319
msgid "`{#}` - The tree object ID (SHA-1 hash) of the commit"
msgstr "`{#}` - 提交的 tree 对象 ID（SHA-1 哈希）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:320
msgid "`{@}` - The commit object ID (SHA-1 hash)"
msgstr "`{@}` - 提交对象 ID（SHA-1 哈希）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:321
msgid ""
"`{/path}` - The content of the file at the specified path in the commit tree"
msgstr "`{/path}` - 提交 tree 中指定路径处文件的内容"

#: src/reference/filters.md:322
msgid ""
"`{#path}` - The object ID (SHA-1 hash) of the tree entry at the specified "
"path"
msgstr "`{#path}` - 指定路径处 tree 条目的对象 ID（SHA-1 哈希）"

#: src/reference/filters.md:324
msgid ""
"Regex capture groups take priority over template variables. If a regex "
"capture group has the same name as a template variable, the capture group "
"value will be used."
msgstr ""
"正则捕获组优先于模板变量。如果某个正则捕获组与模板变量同名，将使用捕获组的值。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:326
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "示例："

#: src/reference/filters.md:327
msgid ""
"```\n"
":\"Message: {#} {@}\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":\"Message: {#} {@}\"\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:330
msgid ""
"This replaces commit messages with \"Message: \" followed by the tree ID and "
"commit ID."
msgstr "这会将提交消息替换为 \"Message: \" 后跟 tree ID 和提交 ID。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:332
msgid "**Combining regex capture groups and template variables:**"
msgstr "**组合正则捕获组和模板变量：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:333
msgid ""
"```\n"
":\"[{type}] {message} (commit: {@})\";\"(?s)^(?P<type>Original) (?P<message>."
"+)$\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":\"[{type}] {message} (commit: {@})\";\"(?s)^(?P<type>Original) (?P<message>."
"+)$\"\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:336
msgid ""
"This combines regex capture groups (`{type}` and `{message}`) with template "
"variables (`{@}` for the commit ID)."
msgstr "这会将正则捕获组（`{type}` 和 `{message}`）与模板变量（表示提交 ID 的 `{@}`）组合使用。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:338
msgid "**Removing text from messages:**"
msgstr "**从消息中移除文本：**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:339
msgid ""
"```\n"
":\"\";\"TODO\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
":\"\";\"TODO\"\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/filters.md:342
msgid ""
"This removes all occurrences of \"TODO\" from commit messages by matching "
"\"TODO\" and replacing it with an empty string. The regex pattern can use `(?"
"s)` to enable dot-all mode (so `.` matches newlines), allowing it to work "
"with multi-line commit messages that include both a subject line and a body."
msgstr ""
"这会通过匹配 \"TODO\" 并将其替换为空字符串，从提交消息中移除所有 \"TODO\"。"
"正则模式可以使用 `(?s)` 启用 dot-all 模式（使 `.` 匹配换行），从而可以处理同时"
"包含主题行和正文的多行提交消息。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:346
msgid "Hook **`:hook=<arg>`**"
msgstr "Hook **`:hook=<arg>`**"

#: src/reference/filters.md:348
msgid ""
"Apply a different filter to each commit in a history, where the per-commit "
"filter is resolved at runtime rather than being fixed at invocation time."
msgstr "对历史中的每个提交应用不同过滤器，其中每提交过滤器会在运行时解析，而不是在调用时固定。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:351
msgid ""
"`<arg>` selects the git notes ref that stores those per-commit filter "
"specifications. When `<arg>` does not start with `refs/`, Josh reads notes "
"from `refs/notes/<arg>`, so `:hook=commits` uses the default git notes ref "
"`refs/notes/commits`. Each note body must contain a valid Josh filter "
"expression for that commit; if a commit has no note in the selected ref, "
"`josh-filter` fails."
msgstr ""
"`<arg>` 选择用于存储这些每提交过滤器规格的 git notes ref。当 `<arg>` 不以 "
"`refs/` 开头时，Josh 会从 `refs/notes/<arg>` 读取 notes，因此 `:hook=commits` "
"会使用默认 git notes ref `refs/notes/commits`。每个 note 正文必须包含该提交的"
"有效 Josh 过滤器表达式；如果某个提交在所选 ref 中没有 note，`josh-filter` 会失败。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:357
msgid "Minimal example:"
msgstr "最小示例："

#: src/reference/filters.md:365
msgid ""
"In this example, the first filtered commit exposes `code/` at the repository "
"root, while the second uses `:pin` to keep `app.js` at its previous contents "
"for that commit only."
msgstr ""
"在此示例中，第一个过滤后的提交会在仓库根目录暴露 `code/`，而第二个提交使用 "
"`:pin` 仅针对该提交保持 `app.js` 为先前内容。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:368
msgid ""
"When using Josh as a library, hook resolution is not tied to git notes. You "
"can provide your own implementation of the `josh_core::cache::FilterHook` "
"trait and attach it with `TransactionContext::with_filter_hook`, which lets "
"your application decide how `filter_for_commit(commit_oid, arg)` resolves "
"the per-commit filter."
msgstr ""
"将 Josh 作为库使用时，hook 解析并不绑定到 git notes。你可以提供自己的 "
"`josh_core::cache::FilterHook` trait 实现，并通过 "
"`TransactionContext::with_filter_hook` 附加它，让应用自行决定 "
"`filter_for_commit(commit_oid, arg)` 如何解析每提交过滤器。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:373
msgid ""
"**Note:** Using `:hook` correctly requires care to preserve josh filter "
"invariants — violating them can produce incorrect or inconsistent results. "
"Most users won't need this filter, but if you have a use case that seems to "
"call for it, we'd love to hear about it! Feel free to open an issue or start "
"a discussion."
msgstr ""
"**注意：** 正确使用 `:hook` 需要谨慎维护 josh 过滤器不变式——违反这些不变式"
"可能产生错误或不一致的结果。大多数用户不需要此过滤器，但如果你有看起来需要它"
"的用例，我们很愿意了解。欢迎打开 issue 或发起讨论。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:378
msgid "Pin tree contents"
msgstr "固定 tree 内容"

#: src/reference/filters.md:380
msgid "Pin revision of a subtree to revision of the parent commit."
msgstr "将子 tree 的修订固定到父提交的修订。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:382
msgid ""
"In practical terms, it means that file and folder updates are \"held off\", "
"and revisions are \"pinned\". If a tree entry already existed in the parent "
"revision, that version will be chosen. Otherwise, the tree entry will not "
"appear in the filtered commit."
msgstr ""
"实际效果是文件和文件夹更新会被 \"held off\"，修订会被 \"pinned\"。如果某个 tree "
"条目已经存在于父修订中，将选择该版本。否则，该 tree 条目不会出现在过滤后的提交中。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:386
msgid "The source of the parent revision is always the first commit parent."
msgstr "父修订的来源始终是第一个提交父项。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:388
msgid ""
"Note that this filter is only practical when used with `:hook` or `workspace."
"josh`, as it should apply per-revision only. Applying `:pin` for the whole "
"history will result in the subtree being excluded from all revisions."
msgstr ""
"注意，此过滤器只有与 `:hook` 或 `workspace.josh` 一起使用时才实用，因为它应"
"仅按修订应用。对整个历史应用 `:pin` 会导致该子 tree 被从所有修订中排除。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:392
msgid ""
"Refer to `pin_filter_workspace.t` and `pin_filter_hook.t` for reference."
msgstr "请参考 `pin_filter_workspace.t` 和 `pin_filter_hook.t`。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:394
msgid "Filter order matters"
msgstr "过滤器顺序很重要"

#: src/reference/filters.md:397
msgid ""
"Filters are applied in the left-to-right order they are given in the filter "
"specification, and they are `not` commutative."
msgstr "过滤器会按照过滤器规格中给定的从左到右顺序应用，并且它们`不`满足交换律。"

#: src/reference/filters.md:400
msgid ""
"For example, this command will filter out just the josh documentation, and "
"store it in a ref named `FILTERED_HEAD`:"
msgstr "例如，此命令会仅过滤出 josh 文档，并将其存储在名为 `FILTERED_HEAD` 的 ref 中："

#: src/reference/filters.md:405
msgid "However, `this` command will produce an empty branch:"
msgstr "然而，`this` 命令会生成一个空分支："

#: src/reference/filters.md:409
msgid ""
"What's happening in the latter command is that because the prefix filter is "
"applied first, the entire `josh` history already lives within the `josh-"
"docs` directory, as it was just transformed to exist there. Thus, to still "
"get the docs, the command would need to be:"
msgstr ""
"后一个命令中发生的情况是：由于 prefix 过滤器先应用，整个 `josh` 历史已经位于 "
"`josh-docs` 目录中，因为它刚刚被转换到那里。因此，如果仍要获得 docs，命令需要是："

#: src/reference/filters.md:415
msgid ""
"which will contain the josh documentation at the base of the tree. We've "
"lost the prefix, what gives?? Because the original git tree was already "
"transformed, and then the subdirectory filter was applied to pull "
"documentation from `josh-docs/docs`, the prefix is gone - it was filtered "
"out again by the subdirectory filter. Thus, the order in which filters are "
"provided is crucial, as each filter further transforms the latest "
"transformation of the tree."
msgstr ""
"这会在 tree 根部包含 josh 文档。前缀怎么没了？因为原始 git tree 已经被转换，"
"随后又应用子目录过滤器从 `josh-docs/docs` 提取文档，所以前缀消失了——它被子目录"
"过滤器再次过滤掉了。因此，提供过滤器的顺序至关重要，因为每个过滤器都会进一步"
"转换 tree 的最新转换结果。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:3
msgid ""
"Experimental features are opt-in and must be enabled at runtime by setting "
"the environment variable `JOSH_EXPERIMENTAL_FEATURES=1`. Their behaviour or "
"syntax may change in future releases."
msgstr ""
"实验性功能需要显式启用，并且必须在运行时设置环境变量 "
"`JOSH_EXPERIMENTAL_FEATURES=1`。它们的行为或语法可能在未来版本中发生变化。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:7
msgid "Filters"
msgstr "过滤器"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:9
msgid "Blob insertion **`:$path=\"content\"`**"
msgstr "Blob 插入 **`:$path=\"content\"`**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:11
msgid ""
"Inserts a new file at `path` in the output tree with the given literal text "
"as its content. No newline is appended automatically. The path argument "
"follows the same quoting rules as other filter arguments: quote with double "
"quotes if the path contains spaces or special characters."
msgstr ""
"在输出 tree 的 `path` 处插入一个新文件，并使用给定字面文本作为其内容。不会"
"自动追加换行符。路径参数遵循与其他过滤器参数相同的引用规则：如果路径包含空格"
"或特殊字符，请使用双引号引用。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:16
msgid ""
"The inverse of `:$path=\"content\"` is `:exclude[::path]`, which removes the "
"inserted file."
msgstr "`:$path=\"content\"` 的反向形式是 `:exclude[::path]`，它会移除插入的文件。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:20
msgid ""
"```\n"
"# Insert a file named \"VERSION\" containing \"1.0\" at the root\n"
":$VERSION=\"1.0\"\n"
"\n"
"# Insert a file whose name contains a space\n"
":$\"release notes.txt\"=\"Initial release\"\n"
"\n"
"# Combine with a subdirectory filter to insert the file alongside existing "
"content\n"
":[:/sub1,:$added.txt=\"hello world\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```\n"
"# 在根目录插入名为 \"VERSION\" 且内容为 \"1.0\" 的文件\n"
":$VERSION=\"1.0\"\n"
"\n"
"# 插入名称包含空格的文件\n"
":$\"release notes.txt\"=\"Initial release\"\n"
"\n"
"# 与子目录过滤器组合，在现有内容旁插入文件\n"
":[:/sub1,:$added.txt=\"hello world\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:31
msgid "Object reference **`:&path`**"
msgstr "对象引用 **`:&path`**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:32
msgid ""
"Reads the git object at `path` (a file or directory) and replaces its "
"content with a text blob containing the object's SHA-1 hash. This turns a "
"real file or tree into a lightweight pointer."
msgstr ""
"读取 `path` 处的 git 对象（文件或目录），并将其内容替换为包含该对象 SHA-1 哈希"
"的文本 blob。这会将真实文件或 tree 转换为轻量指针。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:35
msgid "If `path` does not exist in the input tree, the filter is a no-op."
msgstr "如果 `path` 在输入 tree 中不存在，该过滤器就是 no-op。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:37
msgid ""
"Example: `:&sub1` on a commit where `sub1` is a directory produces a file "
"`sub1` whose content is the 40-character SHA of that directory tree."
msgstr ""
"示例：在 `sub1` 是目录的提交上使用 `:&sub1`，会生成一个文件 `sub1`，其内容是"
"该目录 tree 的 40 字符 SHA。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:40
msgid "Object dereference **`:#path`**"
msgstr "对象解引用 **`:#path`**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:41
msgid ""
"Reads the SHA-1 hash stored as text in the file at `path` and replaces that "
"file with the git object the hash points to (a file or a directory tree). "
"This follows the pointer written by `:&path`."
msgstr ""
"读取 `path` 处文件中以文本形式存储的 SHA-1 哈希，并将该文件替换为该哈希指向的 "
"git 对象（文件或目录 tree）。这会跟随 `:&path` 写入的指针。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:45
msgid ""
"If `path` does not exist the filter is a no-op. If the content is not a "
"valid SHA or the object is not present in the repository, an error is "
"returned."
msgstr ""
"如果 `path` 不存在，该过滤器就是 no-op。如果内容不是有效 SHA，或对象不存在于"
"仓库中，则返回错误。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:48
msgid ""
"Example: given a file `sub1` whose content is the SHA of a directory tree, `:"
"#sub1` replaces that file with the actual directory tree at `sub1`."
msgstr ""
"示例：给定一个文件 `sub1`，其内容是某个目录 tree 的 SHA，`:#sub1` 会将该文件"
"替换为 `sub1` 处的实际目录 tree。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:51
msgid "Object dereference into subdirectory **`:#/path`**"
msgstr "将对象解引用到子目录 **`:#/path`**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:52
msgid ""
"Dereferences the pointer stored at `path` and then extracts the resulting "
"object directly at the repository root, discarding the `path` prefix. This "
"is the typical way to restore content that was previously stored with `:"
"&path`."
msgstr ""
"解引用存储在 `path` 处的指针，然后将得到的对象直接提取到仓库根目录，丢弃 "
"`path` 前缀。这是恢复之前用 `:&path` 存储的内容的典型方式。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:56
msgid ""
"Expands to `:#path:/path`. The canonical printed form is the expanded syntax."
msgstr "会展开为 `:#path:/path`。规范打印形式是展开后的语法。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:58
msgid ""
"Example: `:#/sub1` on a tree where `sub1` holds a SHA of a directory returns "
"that directory's contents at the root, as if `sub1` never existed."
msgstr ""
"示例：在 `sub1` 保存目录 SHA 的 tree 上使用 `:#/sub1`，会在根目录返回该目录的"
"内容，就像 `sub1` 从未存在一样。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:61
msgid "Tree ID capture **`:#path[filter]`**"
msgstr "Tree ID 捕获 **`:#path[filter]`**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:62
msgid ""
"Applies `filter` to the current tree and writes the SHA-1 hash of the "
"resulting tree as a text file at `path`. The filter itself does not appear "
"in the output — only the hash it produces."
msgstr ""
"将 `filter` 应用于当前 tree，并把结果 tree 的 SHA-1 哈希作为文本文件写入 "
"`path`。过滤器本身不会出现在输出中——只有它生成的哈希会出现。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:65
msgid ""
"This lets you record a stable, content-addressed reference to a subtree "
"alongside other files."
msgstr "这允许你在其他文件旁记录一个稳定、按内容寻址的子 tree 引用。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:67
msgid ""
"Example: `:#version.txt[:/sub1]` writes the SHA of the `sub1` directory tree "
"into `version.txt`."
msgstr "示例：`:#version.txt[:/sub1]` 会将 `sub1` 目录 tree 的 SHA 写入 `version.txt`。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:69
msgid "Starlark filter **`:!path/to/script[context filter]`**"
msgstr "Starlark 过滤器 **`:!path/to/script[context filter]`**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:70
msgid ""
"Evaluates a [Starlark](https://github.com/bazelbuild/starlark) script stored "
"in the repository and uses the filter it produces. The script file is loaded "
"from `path` with a `.star` extension appended automatically."
msgstr ""
"求值仓库中存储的 [Starlark](https://github.com/bazelbuild/starlark) 脚本，并"
"使用它生成的过滤器。脚本文件会从 `path` 加载，并自动追加 `.star` 扩展名。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:74
msgid ""
"The optional `[context filter]` scopes the tree that is visible to the "
"script: the context filter is applied to the input tree first, and the "
"result is what the script sees as `tree`. The context filter does not affect "
"the filter that the script returns — it only controls what the script can "
"read."
msgstr ""
"可选的 `[context filter]` 会限定脚本可见的 tree：上下文过滤器会先应用到输入 "
"tree，结果就是脚本看到的 `tree`。上下文过滤器不会影响脚本返回的过滤器——它只"
"控制脚本可以读取什么。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:79
msgid ""
"The script file itself is always included in the output tree alongside "
"whatever the script's filter selects."
msgstr "脚本文件本身始终会与脚本过滤器选中的内容一起包含在输出 tree 中。"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:82
msgid "**Script contract**"
msgstr "**脚本契约**"

#: src/reference/experimental.md:84
msgid ""
"The script must assign a `Filter` value to the variable named `filter`. At "
"the start of execution `filter` is pre-set to a no-op filter, so a minimal "
"script that selects nothing can simply leave it unchanged, or assign a new "
"value:"
msgstr ""
"脚本必须将一个 `Filter` 值赋给名为 `filter` 的变量。执行开始时，`filter` 会被"
"预设为 no-op 过滤器，因此一个什么都不选择的最小脚本可以直接保持它不变，或赋予"
"新值："

#: src/reference/experimental.md:89
