msgstr "创建新的 workspace"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:11
msgid ""
"To create a new workspace in the path `ws/hello` simply clone it as if it "
"already exists:"
msgstr "要在路径 `ws/hello` 创建新的 workspace，只需像它已经存在一样克隆它："

#: src/reference/workspace.md:13
msgid ""
"    $ git clone http://josh/world.git:workspace=ws/hello.git\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ git clone http://josh/world.git:workspace=ws/hello.git\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/workspace.md:15
msgid ""
"`git` will report that you appear to have cloned an empty repository if that "
"path does not yet exist. If you don't get this message it means that the "
"path already exists in the repo but may not yet have configured any path "
"mappings."
msgstr ""
"如果该路径尚不存在，`git` 会报告你似乎克隆了一个空仓库。如果你没有看到这条"
"消息，则表示该路径已经存在于仓库中，但可能尚未配置任何路径映射。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:20
msgid ""
"The next step is to add some path mapping to the `workspace.josh` file in "
"the root of the workspace:"
msgstr "下一步是在 workspace 根目录的 `workspace.josh` 文件中添加一些路径映射："

#: src/reference/workspace.md:23
msgid ""
"    $ cd hello\n"
"    $ echo \"mod/a = :/shared/a\" > workspace.josh\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ cd hello\n"
"    $ echo \"mod/a = :/shared/a\" > workspace.josh\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/workspace.md:26
msgid "And and commit the changes:"
msgstr "然后提交这些变更："

#: src/reference/workspace.md:28
msgid ""
"    $ git add workspace.josh\n"
"    $ git commit -m \"add workspace\"\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ git add workspace.josh\n"
"    $ git commit -m \"add workspace\"\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/workspace.md:31
msgid ""
"If the path did not exist previously, the resulting commit will be a root "
"commit that does not share any history with the `world.git` repo. This means "
"a normal `git push` will be rejected at this point. To get correct history, "
"the resulting commit needs to be a based on the history that already exists "
"in `world.git`. There is however no way to do this locally, because we don't "
"have the data required for this. Also, the resulting tree should contain the "
"contents of `shared/a` mapped to `mod/a` which means it needs to be produced "
"on the server side because we don't have the files to put there."
msgstr ""
"如果该路径之前不存在，生成的提交会是一个 root commit，不与 `world.git` 仓库"
"共享任何历史。这意味着此时普通的 `git push` 会被拒绝。为了获得正确的历史，"
"生成的提交需要基于 `world.git` 中已经存在的历史。然而，本地无法做到这一点，"
"因为我们没有所需的数据。另外，生成的 tree 应包含映射到 `mod/a` 的 `shared/a` "
"内容，这意味着它需要在服务端生成，因为我们本地没有可放入那里的文件。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:40
msgid "To accomplish that push with the create option:"
msgstr "要完成这一点，请使用 create 选项推送："

#: src/reference/workspace.md:45
msgid ""
"**Note**: While it is perfectly possible to use Josh without a code review "
"system, it is strongly recommended to use some form of code review to be "
"able to inspect commits created by Josh before they get into the immutable "
"history of your main repository."
msgstr ""
"**注意**：虽然完全可以在没有代码审查系统的情况下使用 Josh，但强烈建议使用某种"
"形式的代码审查，以便在 Josh 创建的提交进入主仓库不可变历史之前检查它们。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:49
msgid ""
"As the resulting commit is created on the server side we need to get it from "
"the server:"
msgstr "由于生成的提交是在服务端创建的，我们需要从服务端获取它："

#: src/reference/workspace.md:53
msgid ""
"Now you should see `mod/a` populated with the content of the shared code."
msgstr "现在你应该会看到 `mod/a` 已填充共享代码的内容。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:56
msgid "Map a shared path into a workspace"
msgstr "将共享路径映射到 workspace 中"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:59
msgid ""
"To add shared path to a location in the workspace that does not exist yet, "
"first add an entry to the `workspace.josh` file and commit that."
msgstr ""
"要将共享路径添加到 workspace 中尚不存在的位置，先向 `workspace.josh` 文件添加"
"一个条目并提交。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:62
msgid ""
"You can add the mapping at the end of the file using a simple syntax, and "
"rely on josh to rewrite it for you in a canonical way."
msgstr "你可以使用简单语法在文件末尾添加映射，并依赖 josh 为你将其重写为规范形式。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:68
msgid ""
"At this point the path is of course empty, so the commit needs to be pushed "
"to the server. When the same commit is then fetched back it will have the "
"mapped path populated with the shared content."
msgstr ""
"此时该路径当然是空的，因此需要将提交推送到服务端。随后再取回同一个提交时，"
"映射路径将填充共享内容。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:72
msgid ""
"When the commit is pushed, josh will notify you about the rewrite. You can "
"fetch the rewritten commit using the advertised SHA. Alternatively, you can "
"use [git sync](./cli.md#git-sync) which will do it for you."
msgstr ""
"推送提交时，josh 会通知你发生了重写。你可以使用提示的 SHA 获取重写后的提交。"
"或者，也可以使用 [git sync](./cli.md#git-sync)，它会为你完成这一步。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:76
msgid "Publish a non-shared path into a shared location"
msgstr "将非共享路径发布到共享位置"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:79
msgid ""
"The steps here are exactly the same as for the mapping example above. The "
"only difference being that the path already exists in the workspace but not "
"in the shared location."
msgstr ""
"这里的步骤与上面的映射示例完全相同。唯一不同的是，该路径已经存在于 workspace "
"中，但不存在于共享位置中。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:82
msgid "Remove a mapping"
msgstr "移除映射"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:85
msgid ""
"To remove a mapping remove the corresponding entry from the `workspace.josh` "
"file. The content of the previously shared path will stay in the workspace. "
"That means the main repo will have two copies of that path from that point "
"on. Effectively creating a fork of that code."
msgstr ""
"要移除映射，请从 `workspace.josh` 文件中删除对应条目。之前共享路径的内容会"
"保留在 workspace 中。这意味着从此以后主仓库将拥有该路径的两份副本，实际上创建"
"了该代码的一个 fork。"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:89
msgid "Remove a mapped path"
msgstr "移除已映射路径"

#: src/reference/workspace.md:92
msgid ""
"To remove a mapped path as well as it's contents, remove the entry from the "
"`workspace.josh` file and also remove the path inside the workspace using "
"`git rm`."
msgstr ""
"要移除已映射路径及其内容，请从 `workspace.josh` 文件中删除该条目，并使用 "
"`git rm` 移除 workspace 内的该路径。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:1
msgid "Forge Integration"
msgstr "代码托管平台集成"

#: src/reference/forge.md:3
msgid ""
"Forge integration is an **optional** feature that connects `josh` to a code "
"hosting platform (a \"forge\") such as GitHub. It is not required for normal "
"git operations — cloning, pushing, and pulling all work without it, even "
"with private repositories."
msgstr ""
"代码托管平台集成是一项**可选**功能，用于将 `josh` 连接到 GitHub 等代码托管平台"
"（\"forge\"）。普通 git 操作不需要它——即使是私有仓库，克隆、推送和拉取也都能"
"在没有它的情况下工作。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:7
msgid ""
"Forge integration is specifically used for **automatic pull request "
"management** during [stacked changes](../guide/stacked-changes.md) "
"workflows. When you push a stack of commits with `josh publish`, `josh` can "
"automatically create or update one pull request per commit on the forge."
msgstr ""
"代码托管平台集成专门用于在[堆叠式变更](../guide/stacked-changes.md)工作流中"
"进行**自动 pull request 管理**。当你使用 `josh publish` 推送一组提交时，`josh` "
"可以在代码托管平台上为每个提交自动创建或更新一个 pull request。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:12
msgid "GitHub"
msgstr "GitHub"

#: src/reference/forge.md:14
msgid "GitHub is currently the only supported forge."
msgstr "GitHub 是当前唯一支持的代码托管平台。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:16
msgid "Authentication"
msgstr "认证"

#: src/reference/forge.md:18
msgid ""
"`josh` uses GitHub's [device flow](https://docs.github.com/en/apps/oauth-"
"apps/building-oauth-apps/authorizing-oauth-apps#device-flow) for "
"authentication — the same flow used by the official GitHub CLI."
msgstr ""
"`josh` 使用 GitHub 的 [device flow](https://docs.github.com/en/apps/oauth-apps/"
"building-oauth-apps/authorizing-oauth-apps#device-flow) 进行认证——这与官方 "
"GitHub CLI 使用的是同一流程。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:21
msgid "**Log in:**"
msgstr "**登录：**"

#: src/reference/forge.md:27
msgid ""
"This prints a URL and a one-time code. If clipboard access is available the "
"code is also copied automatically, otherwise it is only printed to the "
"terminal. Open the URL in your browser, enter the code, and authorize the "
"application."
msgstr ""
"这会打印一个 URL 和一次性代码。如果可以访问剪贴板，该代码也会自动复制；否则"
"只会打印到终端。请在浏览器中打开该 URL，输入代码并授权应用。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:31
msgid ""
"The token is stored in `~/.config/josh-cli/credentials.json` with `0600` "
"permissions."
msgstr "令牌会以 `0600` 权限存储在 `~/.config/josh-cli/credentials.json` 中。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:33
msgid "**Log out:**"
msgstr "**登出：**"

#: src/reference/forge.md:39
msgid ""
"**Alternatively**, set the `GH_TOKEN` environment variable to a [personal "
"access token](https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-"
"and-data-secure/managing-your-personal-access-tokens). This takes precedence "
"over any stored token and is useful in CI environments:"
msgstr ""
"**或者**，将 `GH_TOKEN` 环境变量设置为[个人访问令牌](https://docs.github.com/"
"en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/managing-your-personal-"
"access-tokens)。它优先于任何已存储令牌，并且适合 CI 环境："

#: src/reference/forge.md:47
msgid "What forge integration enables"
msgstr "代码托管平台集成启用的能力"

#: src/reference/forge.md:49
msgid ""
"Once authenticated, `josh publish` will, in addition to pushing the git refs:"
msgstr "认证后，`josh publish` 除了推送 git ref，还会："

#: src/reference/forge.md:51
msgid "**Create** a pull request for each commit that does not yet have one."
msgstr "为尚无 pull request 的每个提交**创建**一个 pull request。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:52
msgid ""
"**Update** existing pull requests (title, body, base branch) when commits "
"are amended or rebased."
msgstr "当提交被 amend 或 rebase 时，**更新**现有 pull request（标题、正文、base 分支）。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:54
msgid ""
"**Manage draft status** automatically: pull requests whose base branch is "
"not the repository's default branch are marked as drafts, and promoted to "
"\"ready for review\" once they target the default branch directly."
msgstr ""
"自动**管理 draft 状态**：base 分支不是仓库默认分支的 pull request 会被标记为 "
"draft；一旦它们直接以默认分支为目标，就会提升为 \"ready for review\"。"

#: src/reference/forge.md:58
msgid ""
"See the [Stacked changes](../guide/stacked-changes.md) guide for a full "
"walkthrough."
msgstr "完整演练请参见[堆叠式变更](../guide/stacked-changes.md)指南。"

#: src/reference/graphql.md:4
msgid ""
"Josh implements a GraphQL API to query the content of repositories without a "
"need to clone them via a git client."
msgstr "Josh 实现了一个 GraphQL API，可查询仓库内容，而无需通过 git 客户端克隆仓库。"

#: src/reference/graphql.md:7
msgid "The API is exposed at:"
msgstr "API 暴露在："

#: src/reference/graphql.md:9
msgid ""
"    http://hostname/~/graphql/name_of_repo.git\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    http://hostname/~/graphql/name_of_repo.git\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/graphql.md:11
msgid ""
"To explore the API and generated documentation, an interactive GraphQL shell "
"can be found at:"
msgstr "要探索 API 和生成的文档，可以在以下位置找到交互式 GraphQL shell："

#: src/reference/graphql.md:13
msgid ""
"    http://hostname/~/graphiql/name_of_repo.git\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    http://hostname/~/graphiql/name_of_repo.git\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:2
msgid "josh-proxy"
msgstr "josh-proxy"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:5
msgid ""
"**Note**: `josh-proxy` is primarily intended for infrastructure and DevOps "
"use cases — for example, to deploy a shared caching proxy for your team or "
"CI/CD pipelines so that ordinary `git clone` works without any special "
"client tooling. Individual developers can use the [`josh` CLI](../reference/"
"cli.md) instead, which requires no server setup."
msgstr ""
"**注意**：`josh-proxy` 主要面向基础设施和 DevOps 用例——例如，为团队或 CI/CD "
"流水线部署共享缓存代理，使普通 `git clone` 无需任何特殊客户端工具即可工作。"
"个人开发者可以改用无需服务端设置的 [`josh` CLI](../reference/cli.md)。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:11
msgid ""
"Josh provides an HTTP proxy server that can be used with any git hosting "
"service which communicates via HTTP."
msgstr "Josh 提供了一个 HTTP 代理服务器，可与任何通过 HTTP 通信的 git 托管服务一起使用。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:14
msgid ""
"It needs the URL of the upstream server and a local directory to store its "
"data. Optionally, a port to listen on can be specified. For example, running "
"a local `josh-proxy` instance for github.com on port 8000:"
msgstr ""
"它需要上游服务器的 URL，以及用于存储数据的本地目录。也可以指定要监听的端口。"
"例如，在端口 8000 上为 github.com 运行本地 `josh-proxy` 实例："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:18
msgid ""
"    $ docker run -p 8000:8000 -e JOSH_REMOTE=https://github.com -v josh-vol:/"
"data/git joshproject/josh-proxy:latest\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ docker run -p 8000:8000 -e JOSH_REMOTE=https://github.com -v josh-vol:/"
"data/git joshproject/josh-proxy:latest\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:20
msgid ""
"**Note**: While `josh-proxy` is intended to be used with a http upstream it "
"can also proxy for an ssh upstream when `ssh` is used instead of `http` in "
"the url. In that case it will use the ssh private key of the current user "
"(just like git would) and take the username from the downstream http "
"request. This mode of operation can be useful for evaluation or local use by "
"individual developers but should never be used on a normal server deployment."
msgstr ""
"**注意**：虽然 `josh-proxy` 旨在与 http 上游一起使用，但当 URL 中使用 `ssh` "
"而不是 `http` 时，它也可以代理 ssh 上游。在这种情况下，它会使用当前用户的 ssh "
"私钥（就像 git 一样），并从下游 http 请求中取得用户名。这种运行模式可用于评估"
"或个人开发者本地使用，但绝不应在普通服务端部署中使用。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:27
msgid ""
"For a first example of how to make use of josh, just the josh documentation "
"can be checked out as its own repository via this command:"
msgstr "作为使用 josh 的第一个示例，可以通过此命令仅将 josh 文档签出为自己的仓库："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:30 src/reference/proxy.md:70
msgid ""
"    $ git clone http://localhost:8000/josh-project/josh.git:/docs.git\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ git clone http://localhost:8000/josh-project/josh.git:/docs.git\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:32
msgid ""
"**Note**: This URL needs to contain the `.git` suffix twice: once after the "
"original path and once more after the filter spec."
msgstr "**注意**：此 URL 需要包含两次 `.git` 后缀：一次在原始路径之后，另一次在过滤器规格之后。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:35
msgid ""
"`josh-proxy` supports read and write access to the repository, so when "
"making changes to any files in the filtered repository, you can just commit "
"and push them like you are used to."
msgstr ""
"`josh-proxy` 支持对仓库的读写访问，因此在过滤后的仓库中修改任何文件时，你可以"
"像平常一样提交并推送。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:39
msgid ""
"**Note**: The proxy is semantically stateless. The data inside the docker "
"volume is only persisted across runs for performance reasons. This has two "
"important implications for deployment:"
msgstr ""
"**注意**：从语义上讲，代理是无状态的。docker volume 中的数据仅出于性能原因在"
"多次运行之间保留。这对部署有两个重要影响："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:41
msgid ""
"The data does not need to be backed up unless working with very large repos "
"where rebuilding would be very expensive. And 2) Multiple instances of josh-"
"proxy can be used interchangeably for availability or load balancing "
"purposes."
msgstr ""
"除非处理的是重建成本非常高的大型仓库，否则数据无需备份。并且 2）可以互换使用"
"多个 josh-proxy 实例，以实现可用性或负载均衡。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:45
msgid "URL syntax and breakdown"
msgstr "URL 语法和拆解"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:48
msgid "This is the URL of a `josh-proxy` instance:"
msgstr "这是一个 `josh-proxy` 实例的 URL："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:50
msgid ""
"    http://localhost:8000\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    http://localhost:8000\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:52
msgid ""
"This is the repository location on the upstream host on which to perform the "
"filter operations:"
msgstr "这是上游主机上要执行过滤操作的仓库位置："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:56
msgid "This is the set of filter operations to perform:"
msgstr "这是要执行的一组过滤操作："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:60
msgid ""
"Much more information on the available filters and the syntax of all filters "
"is covered in detail in the [filters](./filters.md) section."
msgstr "关于可用过滤器和所有过滤器语法的更多信息，请参见[过滤器](./filters.md)部分。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:63
msgid "Repository naming"
msgstr "仓库命名"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:66
msgid ""
"By default, a git URL is used to point to the remote repository to download "
"_and also_ to dictate how the local repository shall be named.  It's "
"important to learn that the last name in the URL is what the local git "
"client will name the new, local repository. For example:"
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，git URL 用于指向要下载的远程仓库，_同时_也决定本地仓库如何命名。"
"需要注意的是，URL 中的最后一个名称就是本地 git 客户端给新本地仓库使用的名称。"
"例如："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:72
msgid ""
"will create the new repository at directory `docs`, as `docs.git` is the "
"last name in the URL."
msgstr "会在目录 `docs` 处创建新仓库，因为 `docs.git` 是 URL 中的最后一个名称。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:74
msgid ""
"By default, this leads to rather odd-looking repositories when the `prefix` "
"filter is the final filter of a URL:"
msgstr "默认情况下，当 `prefix` 过滤器是 URL 的最后一个过滤器时，这会导致仓库看起来很奇怪："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:77
msgid ""
"    $ git clone http://localhost:8000/josh-project/josh.git:/docs:"
"prefix=josh-docs.git\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ git clone http://localhost:8000/josh-project/josh.git:/docs:"
"prefix=josh-docs.git\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:79
msgid ""
"This will still clone just the josh documentation, but the final directory "
"structure will look like this:"
msgstr "这仍然只会克隆 josh 文档，但最终目录结构会是这样："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:86
msgid ""
"Having the root repository directory name be the fully-specified filter is "
"most likely not what was intended. This results from git's reuse and "
"repurposing of the remote URL, as `prefix=josh-docs` is the final name in "
"the URL. With no other alternatives, this gets used for the repository name."
msgstr ""
"将根仓库目录名设为完整指定的过滤器，通常并不是期望结果。这是因为 git 会复用并"
"重新解释远程 URL，而 `prefix=josh-docs` 是 URL 中的最终名称。在没有其他替代项"
"时，它会被用作仓库名称。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:90
msgid ""
"To explicitly specify a repository name, provide the desired name after the "
"URL when cloning a new repository:"
msgstr "要显式指定仓库名称，请在克隆新仓库时在 URL 后提供所需名称："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:93
msgid ""
"    $ git clone http://localhost:8000/josh-project/josh.git:/docs:"
"prefix=josh-docs.git my-repo\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ git clone http://localhost:8000/josh-project/josh.git:/docs:"
"prefix=josh-docs.git my-repo\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:95
msgid "Retry with backoff"
msgstr "带退避的重试"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:98
msgid ""
"`josh-proxy` automatically retries transient upstream HTTP errors (for "
"example, 5xx responses) with exponential backoff. By default up to 3 retries "
"are attempted, with a delay starting at 1 second and capped at 5 seconds. "
"The number of retries can be configured with the `--http-retry` flag "
"(default: `3`):"
msgstr ""
"`josh-proxy` 会使用指数退避自动重试临时上游 HTTP 错误（例如 5xx 响应）。默认"
"最多尝试 3 次重试，延迟从 1 秒开始，最高限制为 5 秒。可以使用 `--http-retry` "
"标志配置重试次数（默认：`3`）："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:103
msgid ""
"    $ josh-proxy --remote https://github.com --local /data/git --http-retry "
"5\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"    $ josh-proxy --remote https://github.com --local /data/git --http-retry "
"5\n"
"    "

#: src/reference/proxy.md:105
msgid "Set `--http-retry 0` to disable retries entirely."
msgstr "设置 `--http-retry 0` 可完全禁用重试。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:107
msgid "Serving a github repo"
msgstr "提供 github 仓库服务"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:110
msgid ""
"To prompt for authentication, Josh relies on the server requesting it on "
"fetch. When using a server which doesn't need authentication for fetching, "
"Josh will not automatically prompt for authentication when pushing, and it "
"will be impossible to provide credentials for pushing."
msgstr ""
"为了提示认证，Josh 依赖服务端在 fetch 时请求认证。当使用不需要认证即可 fetch "
"的服务器时，Josh 在 push 时不会自动提示认证，也无法为 push 提供凭据。"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:114
msgid ""
"To solve this, you need to pass the `--require-auth` option to josh-proxy. "
"This can be done with `JOSH_EXTRA_OPTS` when using the docker image like so:"
msgstr ""
"为解决此问题，需要向 josh-proxy 传递 `--require-auth` 选项。使用 docker 镜像时，"
"可以像这样通过 `JOSH_EXTRA_OPTS` 完成："

#: src/reference/proxy.md:117
msgid ""
"`docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -e JOSH_EXTRA_OPTS=\"--require-auth\" -e "
"JOSH_REMOTE=https://github.com/josh-project -v josh-vol:$(pwd)/git_data "
"joshproject/josh-proxy:latest `"
msgstr ""
"`docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -e JOSH_EXTRA_OPTS=\"--require-auth\" -e "
"JOSH_REMOTE=https://github.com/josh-project -v josh-vol:$(pwd)/git_data "
"joshproject/josh-proxy:latest `"

#: src/reference/proxy.md:119
msgid ""
"In this example, we serve only the josh-project repositories. Be aware that "
"if you don't add the organisation or repo URL, your instance will be able to "
"serve all of github. You can (and should) restrict it to your repository or "
"organisation by making it part of the URL."
msgstr ""
"在此示例中，我们只提供 josh-project 仓库。请注意，如果不添加组织或仓库 URL，"
"你的实例将能够提供整个 github。你可以（也应该）通过将仓库或组织作为 URL 的一"
"部分来限制范围。"

